  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Ahaziah\u2019s Messengers Meet Elijah"
      title: "Ahaziah\u2019s Messengers Meet Elijah"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Moab rebelled against Israel after the death of Ahab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Ahaziah [the king of Israel] fell through the lattice (grid) in his
        upper chamber which was in Samaria, and became sick [from the injury]. So
        he sent messengers, saying to them, \u201CGo, inquire of Baal-zebub, the
        god of Ekron, if I will recover from this sickness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But the angel of the Lord said to Elijah the Tishbite, \u201CArise,
        go up to meet the messengers of the king of Samaria, and say to them, \u2018Is
        it because there is no God in Israel that you are going to inquire of Baal-zebub,
        the god of Ekron?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Therefore this is what the Lord says: \u2018You [Ahaziah] will not
        leave the bed on which you lie, but you will certainly die.\u2019\u2009\u201D
        So Elijah departed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When the messengers returned to Ahaziah, he said to them, \u201CWhy
        have you returned [so soon]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They replied, \u201CA man came up to meet us and said to us, \u2018Go,
        return to the king who sent you and tell him, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018Is
        it because there is no God in Israel that you send to inquire of Baal-zebub,
        the god of Ekron? Therefore you will not leave the bed on which you lie,
        but you will certainly die.\u2019\u2009\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The king asked them, \u201CWhat was the appearance of the man who
        came up to meet you and said these things to you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They answered him, \u201CHe was a hairy man with a [wide] leather
        band bound around his loins.\u201D And Ahaziah said, \u201CIt is Elijah the
        Tishbite.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the king sent to Elijah a captain of fifty with his fifty [fighting
        men to seize the prophet]. And he went up to him, and behold, he was sitting
        on the top of a hill. And the captain said to him, \u201CMan of God, the
        king says, \u2018Come down.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Elijah replied to the captain of fifty, \u201CSo if I am a man of
        God, then let fire come down from heaven and consume you and your fifty [fighting
        men].\u201D Then fire fell from heaven and consumed him and his fifty.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So King Ahaziah again sent to him another captain of fifty with his
        fifty [fighting men]. And he said to him, \u201CMan of God, thus says the
        king, \u2018Come down quickly.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Elijah answered them, \u201CIf I am a man of God, let fire come down
        from heaven and consume you and your fifty [fighting men].\u201D And the
        fire of God came down from heaven and consumed him and his fifty.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So Ahaziah again sent a captain of a third fifty with his fifty [fighting
        men]. And the third captain of fifty went up and came bowed down on his knees
        before Elijah, and begged him [for compassion] and said to him, \u201CO man
        of God, please let my life and the lives of your servants, these fifty, be
        precious in your sight. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Behold, fire came down from heaven and consumed the first two captains
        of fifty with their fifties; but now let my life be precious in your sight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The angel of the Lord said to Elijah, \u201CGo down with him; do
        not be afraid of him.\u201D So he stood and went down with him to the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Jehoram Reigns over Israel'
      title: Jehoram Reigns over Israel
      number: 16
      content: "Then Elijah said to Ahaziah, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018Since
        you have sent messengers to inquire of Baal-zebub, god of Ekron\u2014is it
        because there is no God in Israel to inquire of His word?\u2014therefore
        you will not leave the bed on which you lie, but will certainly die.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So Ahaziah [the son of King Ahab] died in accordance with the word
        of the Lord which Elijah had spoken. And because he had no son, Jehoram [his
        younger brother] became king [of Israel, the northern kingdom] in his place
        in the second year of Jehoram the son of Jehoshaphat, king of Judah [the
        southern kingdom]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Now the rest of the acts of Ahaziah which he did, are they not written
        in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elijah Taken to Heaven'
      title: Elijah Taken to Heaven
      number: 1
      content: '  When the Lord was about to take Elijah up to heaven by a whirlwind,
        Elijah and Elisha were traveling from Gilgal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Elijah said to Elisha, \u201CPlease stay here, for the Lord has
        sent me to Bethel.\u201D But Elisha replied, \u201CAs the Lord lives and
        as your soul lives, I will not leave you.\u201D So they went down to Bethel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now the sons of the prophets who were at Bethel came out to Elisha
        and said to him, \u201CDo you know that the Lord will take your master away
        from you today?\u201D He said, \u201CYes, I know it; be quiet [about it].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Elijah said to him, \u201CElisha, please stay here, for the Lord
        has sent me to Jericho.\u201D But he said, \u201CAs the Lord lives and as
        your soul lives, I will not leave you.\u201D So they came to Jericho. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The sons of the prophets who were at Jericho approached Elisha and
        said to him, \u201CDo you know that the Lord will take your master away from
        you today?\u201D And he answered, \u201CYes, I know it; be quiet [about it].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Elijah said to him, \u201CPlease stay here, for the Lord has sent
        me to the Jordan.\u201D But he said, \u201CAs the Lord lives and as your
        soul lives, I will not leave you.\u201D So the two of them went on.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Fifty men of the sons of the prophets also went and stood opposite
        them [to watch] at a distance; and the two of them stood by the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And Elijah took his mantle (coat) and rolled it up and struck the
        waters, and they were divided this way and that, so that the two of them
        crossed over on dry ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And when they had crossed over, Elijah said to Elisha, \u201CAsk
        what I shall do for you before I am taken from you.\u201D And Elisha said,
        \u201CPlease let a double portion of your spirit be upon me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "He said, \u201CYou have asked for a difficult thing. However, if
        you see me when I am taken from you, it shall be so for you; but if not,
        it shall not be so.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'As they continued along and talked, behold, a chariot of fire with
        horses of fire [appeared suddenly and] separated the two of them, and Elijah
        went up to heaven in a whirlwind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Elisha saw it and cried out, \u201CMy father, my father, the chariot
        of Israel and its horsemen!\u201D And he no longer saw Elijah. Then he took
        hold of his own clothes and tore them into two pieces [in grief]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He picked up the mantle of Elijah that fell off him, and went back
        and stood by the bank of the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Elisha Succeeds Elijah'
      title: Elisha Succeeds Elijah
      number: 14
      content: "He took the mantle of Elijah that fell from him and struck the waters
        and said, \u201CWhere is the Lord, the God of Elijah?\u201D And when he too
        had struck the waters, they divided this way and that, and Elisha crossed
        over.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When the sons of the prophets who were [watching] opposite at Jericho
        saw him, they said, \u201CThe spirit of Elijah rests on Elisha.\u201D And
        they came to meet him and bowed down to the ground before him [in respect]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then they said to Elisha, \u201CBehold now, there are among your
        servants fifty strong men; please let them go and search for your master.
        It may be that the Spirit of the Lord has taken him up and cast him on some
        mountain or into some valley.\u201D And he said, \u201CYou shall not send
        anyone.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But when they urged him until he was embarrassed [to refuse them],
        he said, \u201CSend them.\u201D So they sent fifty men, and they searched
        for three days but did not find Elijah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "They returned to Elisha while he was staying at Jericho; and he said
        to them, \u201CDid I not tell you, \u2018Do not go\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the men of the city said to Elisha, \u201CLook, this city is
        in a pleasant place, as my lord [Elisha] sees; but the water is bad and the
        land is barren.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "He said, \u201CBring me a new jar, and put salt in it.\u201D So they
        brought it to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Elisha went to the spring of water and threw the salt in it
        and said, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018I [not the salt] have purified
        and healed these waters; there shall no longer be death or barrenness because
        of it.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So the waters have been purified to this day, in accordance with
        the word spoken by Elisha.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Elisha went up from Jericho to Bethel. On the way, young boys
        came out of the city and mocked him and said to him, \u201CGo up, you baldhead!
        Go up, you baldhead!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When he turned around and looked at them, he cursed them in the name
        of the Lord. Then two female bears came out of the woods and tore to pieces
        forty-two of the boys. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Elisha went from there to Mount Carmel, and from there he returned
        to Samaria.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoram Meets Moab Rebellion'
      title: Jehoram Meets Moab Rebellion
      number: 1
      content: '  Jehoram the son of Ahab became king over Israel in Samaria in the
        eighteenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, and reigned twelve years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord, but not like his father and
        mother; for he put away the sacred pillar of Baal that his father had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Nevertheless, he continued in the [idolatrous] sins of Jeroboam the
        son of Nebat, who made Israel sin; he did not depart from them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Mesha the king of Moab was a sheep breeder, and he used to pay
        [an annual tribute] to the king of Israel 100,000 lambs and the wool of 100,000
        rams. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But when Ahab died, the king of Moab rebelled against the king of
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So King Jehoram left Samaria at that time and assembled all [the
        fighting men of] Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then he went and sent word to Jehoshaphat king of Judah, saying,
        \u201CThe king of Moab has rebelled against me. Will you go with me to fight
        against Moab?\u201D And he replied, \u201CI will go; I am as you are, my
        people as your people, my horses as your horses.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Jehoram said, \u201CWhich way shall we go up?\u201D Jehoshaphat answered,
        \u201CThe way through the Wilderness of Edom.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So the king of Israel went with the king of Judah and the king of
        Edom. They made a circuit of seven days\u2019 journey, but there was no water
        for the army or for the cattle that followed them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the king of Israel said, \u201CWe are doomed, for the Lord has
        called these three kings to be handed over to Moab.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Jehoshaphat said, \u201CIs there no prophet of the Lord here
        from whom we may inquire of the Lord?\u201D One of the servants of the king
        of Israel answered, \u201CElisha the son of Shaphat is here, who used to
        pour water over Elijah\u2019s hands.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Jehoshaphat said, \u201CThe word of the Lord is with him.\u201D So
        the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat and the king of Edom went down to Elisha.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now Elisha said to the king of Israel, \u201CWhat business do you
        have with me? Go to the prophets of your [wicked] father [Ahab] and to the
        prophets of your [pagan] mother [Jezebel].\u201D But the king of Israel said
        to him, \u201CNo, for the Lord has called these three kings together to be
        handed over to Moab.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Elisha said, \u201CAs the Lord of hosts (armies) lives, before whom
        I stand, were it not that I have regard for Jehoshaphat king of Judah, I
        would not look at you nor see you [king of Israel]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But now bring me a musician.\u201D And it came about while the musician
        played, that the hand (power) of the Lord came upon Elisha. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He said, \u201CThus says the Lord, \u2018Make this valley (the Arabah)
        full of trenches.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For thus says the Lord, \u2018You will not see wind or rain, yet
        that valley will be filled with water, so you and your cattle and your other
        animals may drink. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'This is but a simple thing in the sight of the Lord; He will also
        hand over the Moabites to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "You shall strike every fortified city and every choice (principal)
        city, and cut down every good tree and stop up all sources of water, and
        ruin every good piece of land with stones.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'It happened in the morning, when the sacrifice was offered, that
        suddenly water came [miraculously] from the area of Edom, and the country
        was filled with water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now all the Moabites heard that the [three] kings had come up to
        fight against them, and all who were able to put on armor, as well as those
        who were older, were summoned and stood [together in battle formation] at
        the border. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When they got up early the next morning, the sun shone on the water,
        and the Moabites saw the water across from them as red as blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And they said, \u201CThis is blood! Clearly the kings have fought
        together, and have killed one another. Now then, Moab, to the spoil [and
        the plunder of the dead soldiers]!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But when they came to the camp of Israel, the Israelites rose up
        and struck the Moabites, so that they fled before them; and they went forward
        into the land, killing the Moabites [as they went]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "They destroyed the [walls of the] cities, and each man threw a stone
        on every piece of good land, covering it [with stones]. And they stopped
        up all the springs of water and cut down all the good trees, until they left
        nothing in Kir-hareseth [Moab\u2019s capital city] but its stones. Then the
        [stone] slingers surrounded the city and destroyed it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'When the king of Moab saw that the battle was too fierce for him,
        he took with him seven hundred swordsmen to break through to the king of
        Edom; but they could not. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then the king of Moab took his eldest son, who was to reign in his
        place, and offered him [publicly] as a burnt offering [to Chemosh] on the
        [city] wall [horrifying everyone]. And there was great wrath against Israel,
        and Israel\u2019s allies [Judah and Edom] withdrew from King Jehoram and
        returned to their own land."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Widow\u2019s Oil"
      title: "The Widow\u2019s Oil"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now one of the wives of a man of the sons of the prophets cried
        out to Elisha [for help], saying \u201CYour servant my husband is dead, and
        you know that your servant [reverently] feared the Lord; but the creditor
        is coming to take my two sons to be his slaves [in payment for a loan].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Elisha said to her, \u201CWhat shall I do for you? Tell me, what
        do you have [of value] in the house?\u201D She said, \u201CYour maidservant
        has nothing in the house except a [small] jar of [olive] oil.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then he said, \u201CGo, borrow containers from all your neighbors,
        empty containers\u2014and not just a few. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then you shall go in and shut the door behind you and your sons,
        and pour out [the oil you have] into all these containers, and you shall
        set aside each one when it is full.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So she left him and shut the door behind her and her sons; they were
        bringing her the containers as she poured [the oil]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When the containers were all full, she said to her son, \u201CBring
        me another container.\u201D And he said to her, \u201CThere is not a one
        left.\u201D Then the oil stopped [multiplying]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Shunammite Woman'
      title: The Shunammite Woman
      number: 7
      content: "Then she came and told the man of God. He said, \u201CGo, sell the
        oil and pay your debt, and you and your sons can live on the rest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now there came a day when Elisha went over to Shunem, where there
        was a prominent and influential woman, and she persuaded him to eat a meal.
        Afterward, whenever he passed by, he stopped there for a meal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "She said to her husband, \u201CBehold, I sense that this is a holy
        man of God who frequently passes our way. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Please, let us make a small, fully-walled upper room [on the housetop]
        and put a bed there for him, with a table, a chair, and a lampstand. Then
        whenever he comes to visit us, he can turn in there.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'One day he came there and turned in to the upper room and lay down
        to rest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And he said to Gehazi his servant, \u201CCall this Shunammite.\u201D
        So he called her and she stood before him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now he said to Gehazi, \u201CSay to her now, \u2018You have gone
        to all this trouble for us; what can I do for you? Would you like to be mentioned
        to the king or to the captain of the army?\u2019\u2009\u201D She answered,
        \u201CI live among my own people [in peace and security and need no special
        favors].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Later Elisha said, \u201CWhat then is to be done for her?\u201D Gehazi
        answered, \u201CWell, she has no son and her husband is old.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He said, \u201CCall her.\u201D So Gehazi called her, and she [came
        and] stood in the doorway. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Elisha said, \u201CAt this season next year, you will embrace a son.\u201D
        She said, \u201CNo, my lord. O man of God, do not lie to your maidservant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: "17: The Shunammite\u2019s Son"
      title: "The Shunammite\u2019s Son"
      number: 17
      content: 'But the woman conceived and gave birth to a son at that season the
        next year, just as Elisha had said to her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When the child was grown, the day came that he went out to his father,
        to the reapers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But he said to his father, \u201CMy head, my head.\u201D The man
        said to his servant, \u201CCarry him to his mother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When he had carried and brought him to his mother, he sat on her
        lap until noon, and then he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'She went up and laid him on the bed of the man of God, and shut the
        door [of the small upper room] behind him and left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then she called to her husband and said, \u201CPlease send me one
        of the servants and one of the donkeys, so that I may run to the man of God
        and return.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He said, \u201CWhy are you going to him today? It is neither the
        New Moon nor the Sabbath.\u201D And she said, \u201CIt will be all right.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then she saddled the donkey and said to her servant, \u201CDrive
        [the animal] fast; do not slow down the pace for me unless I tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So she set out and came to the man of God at Mount Carmel.  When
        the man of God saw her at a distance, he said to Gehazi his servant, \u201CLook,
        there is the Shunammite woman. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Please run now to meet her and ask her, \u2018Is it well with you?
        Is it well with your husband? Is it well with the child?\u2019\u2009\u201D
        And she answered, \u201CIt is well.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "When she came to the mountain to the man of God, she took hold of
        his feet. Gehazi approached to push her away; but the man of God said, \u201CLet
        her alone, for her soul is desperate and troubled within her; and the Lord
        has hidden the reason from me and has not told me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then she said, \u201CDid I ask for a son from my lord? Did I not
        say, \u2018Do not give me false hope\u2019?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then he said to Gehazi, \u201CGird up your loins (prepare now!) and
        take my staff in your hand, and go [to the woman\u2019s house]; if you meet
        any man [along the way], do not greet him and if a man greets you, do not
        [stop to] answer him; and lay my staff on the face of the boy [as soon as
        you reach the house].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "The mother of the child said, \u201CAs the Lord lives and as your
        soul lives, I will not leave you.\u201D So Elisha arose and followed her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Gehazi went on ahead of them and laid the staff on the boy\u2019s
        face, but there was no sound or response [from the boy]. So he turned back
        to meet Elisha and told him, \u201CThe boy has not awakened (revived).\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'When Elisha came into the house, the child was dead and lying on
        his bed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So he went in, shut the door behind the two of them, and prayed to
        the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then he went up and lay on the child and put his mouth on his mouth,
        his eyes on his eyes, and his hands on his hands. And as he stretched himself
        out on him and held him, the boy\u2019s skin became warm. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Then he returned and walked in the house once back and forth, and
        went up [again] and stretched himself out on him; and the boy sneezed seven
        times and he opened his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then Elisha called Gehazi and said, \u201CCall this Shunammite.\u201D
        So he called her. And when she came to him, he said, \u201CPick up your son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: The Poisonous Stew'
      title: The Poisonous Stew
      number: 37
      content: 'She came and fell at his feet, bowing herself to the ground [in respect
        and gratitude]. Then she picked up her son and left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Elisha came back to Gilgal during a famine in the land. The sons
        of the prophets were sitting before him, and he said to his servant, \u201CPut
        on the large pot and cook stew for the sons of the prophets.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Then one [of them] went into the field to gather herbs, and found
        a wild vine and gathered from it a lapful of wild gourds, and came and cut
        them up into the pot of stew, although they did not know what they were. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "So they served it for the men to eat. But as they ate the stew, they
        cried out, \u201CO man of God, there is death in the pot.\u201D And they
        could not eat it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "But he said, \u201CBring flour.\u201D And he threw it into the pot
        and said, \u201CServe it for the people so that they may eat.\u201D Then
        there was nothing harmful in the pot.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Now [at another time] a man from Baal-shalisha came and brought the
        man of God bread of the first fruits, twenty loaves of barley bread, and
        fresh ears of grain [in the husk] in his sack. And Elisha said, \u201CGive
        it to the people [affected by the famine] so that they may eat.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "His servant said, \u201CHow am I to set [only] this before a hundred
        [hungry] men?\u201D He said, \u201CGive it to the people so that they may
        eat, for thus says the Lord, \u2018They shall eat and have some left.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: So he set it before them, and they ate and left some, in accordance
        with the word of the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Naaman Is Healed'
      title: Naaman Is Healed
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Naaman, commander of the army of the king of Aram (Syria),
        was considered a great man by his king, and was highly respected because
        through Naaman the Lord had given victory to Aram (Syria). He was also a
        man of courage, but he was a leper. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Arameans (Syrians) had gone out in bands [as raiders] and had
        taken captive a little girl from the land of Israel; and she waited on Naaman\u2019s
        wife [as a servant]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "She said to her mistress, \u201CI wish that my master [Naaman] were
        with the prophet who is in Samaria! Then he would heal him of his leprosy.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Naaman went in and told his master [the king], \u201CThe girl who
        is from the land of Israel said such and such.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the king of Aram (Syria) said, \u201CGo now, and I will send
        a letter to the king of Israel (Jehoram the son of Ahab).\u201D So he left
        and took with him ten talents of silver and 6,000 shekels of gold, and ten
        changes of clothing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he brought the letter to the king of Israel. It said, \u201CAnd
        now when this letter comes to you, I will have sent my servant Naaman to
        you, so that you may heal him of his leprosy.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When the king of Israel read the letter, he tore his clothes [in
        shock and outrage at the request] and said, \u201CAm I God, to kill and to
        make alive, that this man sends to me [a request] to heal a man of his leprosy?
        Just consider [what he is asking] and see how he is seeking an opportunity
        [for a battle] with me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now when Elisha the man of God heard that the king of Israel had
        torn his clothes, he sent word to the king, asking, \u201CWhy have you torn
        your clothes? Just let Naaman come to me, and he shall know that there is
        a [true] prophet in Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Naaman came with his horses and chariots and stopped at the entrance
        of Elisha\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Elisha sent a messenger to him, saying, \u201CGo and wash in the
        Jordan seven times, and your flesh will be restored to you and you will be
        clean.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Naaman was furious and went away and said, \u201CIndeed! I thought
        \u2018He would at least come out to [see] me and stand and call on the name
        of the Lord his God, and wave his hand over the place [of leprosy] and heal
        the leper.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Are not Abana and Pharpar, the rivers of Damascus [in Aram], better
        than all the waters of Israel? Could I not wash in them and be clean?\u201D
        So he turned and went away in a rage. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then his servants approached and said to him, \u201CMy father, if
        the prophet had told you to do some great thing, would you not have done
        it? How much more then, when he has said to you, \u2018Wash, and be clean?\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "14: Gehazi\u2019s Greed"
      title: "Gehazi\u2019s Greed"
      number: 14
      content: 'So he went down and plunged himself into the Jordan seven times,
        just as the man of God had said; and his flesh was restored like that of
        a little child and he was clean.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Naaman returned to the man of God, he and all the people in
        his group, and stood before him. He said, \u201CBehold, I know that there
        is no God in all the earth, except in Israel; so now accept a blessing and
        gift from your servant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Elisha said, \u201CAs the Lord lives, before whom I stand, I
        will accept nothing.\u201D He urged him to take it, but Elisha refused. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Naaman said, \u201CIf not, then please, let your servant be given
        a load of earth for a team of mules; for [from this day on] your servant
        will no longer offer a burnt offering nor a sacrifice to other gods, but
        only to the Lord, [the God of Israel]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "In this matter may the Lord pardon your servant: when my master [the
        king] goes into the house of [his god] Rimmon to worship there, and he leans
        on my hand and I bow in the house of Rimmon, when I bow down in the house
        of Rimmon, may the Lord pardon your servant in this matter [of attending
        the king when he worships].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Elisha said to him, \u201CGo in peace.\u201D So Naaman departed and
        was a good distance away from him,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "when Gehazi, the servant of Elisha the man of God, said, \u201CMy
        master has spared this Naaman the Aramean (Syrian), by not accepting from
        him what he brought. As the Lord lives, I will run after him and get something
        from him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So Gehazi pursued Naaman. When Naaman saw someone running after him,
        he got down from the chariot to meet him and said, \u201CIs all well?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And he said, \u201CAll is well. My master has sent me to say, \u2018Just
        now two young men of the sons of the prophets have come to me from the hill
        country of Ephraim. Please give them a talent of silver and two changes of
        clothes.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Naaman said, \u201CPlease take two talents.\u201D And he urged him
        [to accept], and tied up two talents of silver in two bags with two changes
        of clothes and gave them to two of his servants; and they carried them in
        front of Gehazi. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When he came to the hill, he took them from their hand and put them
        in the house [for safekeeping]; and he sent the men away, and they left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then he went in and stood before his master. Elisha asked him, \u201CWhere
        have you been, Gehazi?\u201D He said, \u201CYour servant went nowhere.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Elisha said to him, \u201CDid my heart not go with you, when the
        man turned from his chariot to meet you? Is it a [proper] time to accept
        money and clothing and olive orchards and vineyards and sheep and oxen and
        male and female servants? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Therefore, the leprosy of Naaman shall cling to you and to your descendants
        forever.\u201D So Gehazi departed from his presence, a leper as white as
        snow."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Axe Head Recovered'
      title: The Axe Head Recovered
      number: 1
      content: "  Now the sons of the prophets said to Elisha, \u201CLook now, the
        place where we live near you is too small for us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Please let us go to the Jordan [River] and let each man take from
        there a beam [for the building]; and let us make a place there for ourselves
        where we may live.\u201D And he answered, \u201CGo.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then one said, \u201CPlease be willing to go with your servants.\u201D
        So he answered, \u201CI shall go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So he went with them; and when they came to the Jordan, they cut
        down [some of] the trees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But it happened that as one was cutting down a beam, the axe head
        fell into the water; and he cried out and said, \u201COh no, my master! It
        was borrowed!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The man of God said, \u201CWhere did it fall?\u201D When he showed
        him the place, Elisha cut off a stick and threw it in there, and made the
        iron [axe head] float. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Arameans Plot to Capture Elisha'
      title: The Arameans Plot to Capture Elisha
      number: 7
      content: "He said, \u201CPick it up for yourself.\u201D So he reached out with
        his hand and took it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now the king of Aram (Syria) was making war against Israel, and he
        consulted with his servants, saying, \u201CMy camp shall be in such and such
        a place.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The man of God sent word to the king of Israel saying, \u201CBe careful
        not to pass by this place, because the Arameans are pulling back to there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then the king of Israel sent word to the place about which Elisha
        had warned him; so he guarded himself there repeatedly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now the heart of the king of Aram (Syria) was enraged over this thing.
        He called his servants and said to them, \u201CWill you not tell me which
        of us is helping the king of Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "One of his servants said, \u201CNone [of us is helping him], my lord,
        O king; but Elisha, the prophet who is in Israel, tells the king of Israel
        the words that you speak in your bedroom.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So he said, \u201CGo and see where he is, so that I may send [men]
        and seize him.\u201D And he was told, \u201CHe is in Dothan.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So he sent horses and chariots and a powerful army there. They came
        by night and surrounded the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The servant of the man of God got up early and went out, and behold,
        there was an army with horses and chariots encircling the city. Elisha\u2019s
        servant said to him, \u201COh no, my master! What are we to do?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Elisha answered, \u201CDo not be afraid, for those who are with us
        are more than those who are with them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Elisha prayed and said, \u201CLord, please, open his eyes that
        he may see.\u201D And the Lord opened the servants eyes and he saw; and behold,
        the mountain was full of horses and chariots of fire surrounding Elisha. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When the Arameans came down to him, Elisha prayed to the Lord and
        said, \u201CPlease strike this people (nation) with blindness.\u201D And
        God struck them with blindness, in accordance with Elisha\u2019s request. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Elisha said to the Arameans, \u201CThis is not the way, nor
        is this the city. Follow me and I will lead you to the man whom you are seeking.\u201D
        And he led them to Samaria.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "When they had come into Samaria, Elisha said, \u201CLord, open the
        eyes of these men, so that they may see.\u201D And the Lord opened their
        eyes and they saw. Behold, they were in the midst of Samaria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "When the king of Israel (Jehoram) saw them, he said to Elisha, \u201CMy
        father, shall I kill them? Shall I kill them?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Elisha answered, \u201CYou shall not kill them. Would you kill those
        you have taken captive with your sword and bow? Serve them bread and water,
        so that they may eat and drink, and go back to their master [King Ben-hadad].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "23: The Siege of Samaria\u2014Cannibalism"
      title: "The Siege of Samaria\u2014Cannibalism"
      number: 23
      content: 'So the king prepared a great feast for them; and when they had eaten
        and drunk he sent them away, and they went to their master. And the marauding
        bands of Aram did not come into the land of Israel again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But it came about after this, that Ben-hadad king of Aram (Syria)
        gathered his whole army together and went up and besieged Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now there was a great famine in Samaria; and they besieged it until
        a donkey\u2019s head was sold for eighty shekels of silver, and a fourth
        of a kab of dove\u2019s dung for five shekels of silver. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "As the king of Israel (Jehoram) was passing by on the [city] wall
        a woman cried out to him, \u201CHelp, my lord, O king!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "He said, \u201CIf the Lord does not help you, from where shall I
        get you help? From the threshing floor, or from the wine press?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And the king said to her, \u201CWhat is the matter with you?\u201D
        She answered, \u201CThis woman said to me, \u2018Give your son so we may
        eat him today, and we will eat my son tomorrow.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So we cooked my son and ate him. The next day I said to her, \u2018Give
        your son so that we may eat him\u2019; but she had hidden her son.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "When the king heard the woman\u2019s words, he tore his clothes\u2014now
        he was still walking along on the wall\u2014and the people looked [at him],
        and he had on sackcloth underneath [his royal robe] next to his skin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then he said, \u201CMay God do so to me and more also, if the head
        of Elisha the son of Shaphat remains on him today!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Now Elisha was sitting in his house, and the elders were sitting
        with him. And the king sent a man ahead of him [to behead Elisha]; but before
        the messenger arrived, Elisha told the elders, \u201CDo you see how this
        son of [Jezebel] a murderer has sent [a man] to remove my head? Look, when
        the messenger comes, shut the door and hold it securely against him. Is not
        the sound of his master\u2019s feet [just] behind him?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "While Elisha was still talking with them, the messenger came down
        to him [followed by the king] and the king said, \u201CThis evil [situation]
        is from the Lord! Why should I wait for [help from] the Lord any longer?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elisha Promises Food'
      title: Elisha Promises Food
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Elisha said, \u201CHear the word of the Lord. Thus says the
        Lord, \u2018Tomorrow about this time a measure of finely-milled flour will
        sell for a shekel, and two measures of barley for a shekel, at the gate of
        Samaria.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "2: Four Lepers Relate Arameans\u2019 Flight"
      title: "Four Lepers Relate Arameans\u2019 Flight"
      number: 2
      content: "Then the royal officer on whose arm the king leaned answered the
        man of God and said, \u201CIf the Lord should make windows in heaven [for
        the rain], could this thing take place?\u201D Elisha said, \u201CBehold,
        you will see it with your own eyes, but [because you doubt] you will not
        eat of it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now four men who were lepers were at the entrance of the [city\u2019s]
        gate; and they said to one another, \u201CWhy should we sit here until we
        die? "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "If we say, \u2018We will enter the city\u2019\u2014then the famine
        is in the city and we will die there; and if we sit still here, we will also
        die. So now come, let us go over to the camp of the Arameans (Syrians). If
        they let us live, we will live; and if they kill us, we will only die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So they got up at twilight to go to the Aramean camp. But when they
        came to the edge of the camp, there was no one there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For the Lord had caused the Aramean army to hear the sound of chariots,
        and the sound of horses, the sound of a great army. They had said to one
        another, \u201CThe king of Israel has hired against us the kings of the Hittites,
        and the kings of the Egyptians, to come [and fight] against us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So the Arameans set out and fled during the twilight, and left their
        tents, horses, and donkeys, even left the camp just as it was, and fled for
        their lives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When these lepers came to the edge of the camp, they went into one
        tent and ate and drank, and carried away from there silver, gold, and clothing,
        and went and hid them. Then they went back and entered another tent and carried
        [some valuable things] from there also, and went and hid them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then they said one to another, \u201CWe are not doing the right thing.
        This is a day of good news, yet we are keeping silent. If we wait until the
        morning light, some punishment [for not reporting this now] will come on
        us. So now come, let us go and tell the king\u2019s household.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So they came and called to the gatekeepers of the city. They told
        them, \u201CWe went to the camp of the Arameans (Syrians), and behold, there
        was no one there, nor the sound of man there\u2014only the horses and donkeys
        tied up, and the tents [had been left] just as they were.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the gatekeepers called out and it was reported to the king\u2019s
        household inside [the city]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the king got up in the night and said to his servants, \u201CI
        will tell you what the Arameans have done to us. They know that we are hungry;
        so they have left the camp to hide themselves in the open country, thinking,
        \u2018When they come out of the city, we shall take them alive and get into
        the city.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "One of his servants replied, \u201CPlease let some men take five
        of the horses which remain inside the city. Consider this: [if they are caught
        then at worst] they will be like all the people of Israel who are left in
        the city; [even if they are killed then] they will be like all the people
        of Israel who have already died. So let us send [them] and see [what happens].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Promise Fulfilled'
      title: The Promise Fulfilled
      number: 14
      content: "So they took two chariots with horses, and the king sent them after
        the Aramean army, saying, \u201CGo and see.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They went after them to the Jordan, and all the road was entirely
        littered with clothing and equipment which the Arameans (Syrians) had thrown
        away when they hurriedly fled. And the messengers returned and told the king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the people [of Israel] went out and plundered the camp of the
        Arameans. So [goods were so plentiful that] a measure of finely-milled flour
        [was sold] for a shekel, and two measures of barley for a shekel, in accordance
        with the word of the Lord [as spoken through Elisha]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now the king had appointed the royal officer on whose arm he leaned
        to be in charge of the [city] gate; and the [starving] people trampled him
        at the gate [as they struggled to get through for food], and he died, just
        as the man of God had foretold when the king came down to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "It happened just as [Elisha] the man of God had spoken to the king,
        saying, \u201CTwo measures of barley will be sold for a shekel and a measure
        of finely-milled flour for a shekel tomorrow about this time at the gate
        of Samaria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The royal officer had answered the man of God and said, \u201CNow
        behold, [even] if the Lord should make windows in heaven, could such a thing
        happen?\u201D And Elisha had answered, \u201CYou will see it with your own
        eyes, but [because of your doubt] you will not eat it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And so it happened to him; for the people trampled him at the gate,
        and he died.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The King Restores the Shunammite\u2019s Land"
      title: "The King Restores the Shunammite\u2019s Land"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Elisha had said to the [Shunammite] woman whose son he had
        restored to life, \u201CPrepare and go, you and your household, and stay
        temporarily wherever you can; for the Lord has called for a famine, and moreover,
        it will come on the land [and continue] for seven years.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So the woman set out and did everything in accordance with the word
        of the man of God. She and her household went and stayed temporarily as foreigners
        in the land of the Philistines for seven years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'At the end of the seven years the woman returned from the land of
        the Philistines; and she went to appeal to the king [of Israel] for her house
        and for her land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now the king was talking with Gehazi, the servant of the man of God,
        saying, \u201CTell me all the great things that Elisha has done.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And [just] as Gehazi was telling the king how Elisha had restored
        the dead to life, behold, the woman whose son he had restored to life appealed
        to the king for her house and for her land. And Gehazi said, \u201CMy lord,
        O king, this is the woman and this is her son, whom Elisha restored to life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Elisha Predicts Evil from Hazael'
      title: Elisha Predicts Evil from Hazael
      number: 6
      content: "When the king asked the woman, she told him [everything]. So the
        king appointed for her a certain high official, saying, \u201CRestore everything
        that was hers, including all the produce of the field since the day that
        she left the land until now.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now Elisha came to Damascus, and Ben-hadad king of Aram (Syria) was
        sick; and he was told, \u201CThe man of God has come here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the king said to Hazael, \u201CTake a gift with you and go to
        meet the man of God, and inquire of the Lord by him, saying, \u2018Will I
        recover from this illness?\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Hazael went to meet Elisha and took a gift with him of every good
        thing of Damascus, forty camels\u2019 loads; and he came and stood before
        him and said, \u201CYour son Ben-hadad king of Aram has sent me to you, asking,
        \u2018Will I recover from this illness?\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Elisha said to him, \u201CGo, say to him, \u2018You will certainly
        recover,\u2019 but the Lord has shown me that he will certainly die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Elisha stared steadily at Hazael until he was embarrassed, and then
        the man of God wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Hazael said, \u201CWhy are you weeping, my lord?\u201D He answered,
        \u201CBecause I know the evil that you will do to the sons (descendants)
        of Israel. You will set their strongholds on fire, kill their young men with
        the sword, smash their children to pieces, and rip up their pregnant women.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Hazael said, \u201CSurely not! For what is your servant, who
        is nothing more than a dog, that he would do this monstrous thing?\u201D
        And Elisha answered, \u201CThe Lord has shown me that you will be king over
        Aram.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Hazael departed from Elisha and came to his master, who said
        to him, \u201CWhat did Elisha say to you?\u201D And he answered, \u201CHe
        told me you would certainly recover.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Another Jehoram Reigns in Judah'
      title: Another Jehoram Reigns in Judah
      number: 15
      content: "But the next day Hazael took the bedspread and dipped it in water
        and covered the king\u2019s face, so that he died. And Hazael became king
        in his place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now in the fifth year of Joram (Jehoram) the son of Ahab king of
        Israel, when Jehoshaphat was king of Judah, Jehoram the son of Jehoshaphat
        king of Judah became king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He was thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned for
        eight years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He walked in the ways of the kings of Israel, just as the house of
        Ahab had done, for [Athaliah] the daughter of Ahab became his wife. He did
        evil in the sight of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Yet for the sake of His servant David the Lord was not willing to
        destroy Judah, since He had promised to give him a lamp (enthroned descendant)
        through his sons always.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In his days Edom revolted from the rule of Judah, and set up a king
        over themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So Jehoram [king of Judah] went over to Zair [in Edom] with all his
        chariots. He set out by night and struck down the Edomites who had surrounded
        him and the captains of his chariots; but the people [of his army] fled to
        their tents. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Edom revolted against Judah to this day. Then Libnah revolted
        at the same time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Ahaziah Succeeds Jehoram in Judah'
      title: Ahaziah Succeeds Jehoram in Judah
      number: 23
      content: 'The rest of the acts of Jehoram and everything that he did, are they
        not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Jehoram slept with his fathers [in death] and was buried with them
        in the City of David. Ahaziah his son became king in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'In the twelfth year of Joram (Jehoram) the son of Ahab king of Israel,
        Ahaziah the son of Jehoram king of Judah began to reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Ahaziah was twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned
        one year in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Athaliah, the granddaughter
        of Omri king of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He walked in the ways of the house of Ahab and did evil in the sight
        of the Lord, as did the house of Ahab, for he was a son-in-law of the house
        of Ahab.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Ahaziah went with Joram the son of Ahab to battle against Hazael
        king of Aram (Syria) in Ramoth-gilead; and the Arameans wounded Joram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: King Joram returned to Jezreel to be healed of the wounds which the
        Arameans had inflicted on him at Ramah when he fought against Hazael king
        of Aram. And Ahaziah the son of Jehoram king of Judah went down to see Joram
        the son of Ahab in Jezreel, because he was sick.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehu Reigns over Israel'
      title: Jehu Reigns over Israel
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Elisha the prophet called one of the sons of the prophets and
        said to him, \u201CGird up your loins (prepare for action), take this flask
        of oil in your hand and go to Ramoth-gilead. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When you arrive there, look for Jehu the son of Jehoshaphat the son
        of Nimshi, and go in and have him arise from among his brothers, and take
        him into an inner room. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then take the flask of oil and pour it on his head and say, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord: \u201CI have anointed you king over Israel.\u201D\u2009\u2019
        Then open the door and flee and do not delay.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So the young man, the servant of the prophet, went to Ramoth-gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When he arrived, the captains of the army were sitting [outside];
        and he said, \u201CI have a message for you, O captain.\u201D Jehu said,
        \u201CTo which one of us?\u201D And he said, \u201CFor you, O captain.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Jehu got up, and they went into the house. And he poured the oil
        on Jehu\u2019s head and said to him, \u201CThus says the Lord, the God of
        Israel: \u2018I have anointed you king over the people of the Lord, over
        Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You shall strike the house of Ahab your master, so that I may avenge
        the blood of My servants the prophets, and the blood of all the servants
        of the Lord, [who have died] at the hands of Jezebel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the entire house of Ahab shall perish, and I will cut off from
        Ahab every male, both bond and free, in Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will make the house of Ahab like the house of Jeroboam the son
        of Nebat, and like the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the dogs will eat Jezebel in the territory of Jezreel, and there
        will be no one to bury her.\u2019\u2009\u201D Then he opened the door and
        fled.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When Jehu came out to the servants of his master, one said to him,
        \u201CIs all well? Why did this madman come to you?\u201D And he said to
        them, \u201CYou know [very well] the man and his talk.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And they said, \u201CIt is a lie; tell us now.\u201D And he said,
        \u201CThus and thus he spoke to me, saying, \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CI
        have anointed you king over Israel.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Jehoram (Joram) Is Assassinated'
      title: Jehoram (Joram) Is Assassinated
      number: 13
      content: "Then they hurried and each man took his garment and placed it [as
        a cushion] under Jehu on the top of the [outside] stairs, and blew the trumpet,
        saying, \u201CJehu is king!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Jehu the son of Jehoshaphat, the son of Nimshi, conspired against
        Joram [to dethrone and kill him]. Now Joram with all Israel was protecting
        Ramoth-gilead against Hazael king of Aram (Syria), '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "but King Joram had returned to Jezreel to heal from the wounds which
        the Arameans had inflicted on him when he fought with Hazael king of Aram.
        So Jehu said, \u201CIf this is your intent, let no one survive and leave
        the city (Ramoth-gilead) to go and tell of the plan in Jezreel [the capital].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Jehu rode in a chariot and went to Jezreel, for Joram was lying
        there. And Ahaziah king of Judah had come down to see Joram.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now the watchman was standing on the tower in Jezreel and he saw
        the crowd with Jehu as he approached, and said, \u201CI see a company.\u201D
        And Joram said, \u201CSend a horseman to meet them and have him ask, \u2018Do
        you come in peace?\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So the horseman went to meet him and said, \u201CThus says the king:
        \u2018Do you come in peace?\u2019\u2009\u201D And Jehu said, \u201CWhat have
        you to do with peace? Rein in behind me.\u201D And the watchman reported,
        \u201CThe messenger approached them, but he has not returned.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Joram sent out a second horseman, who approached them and said,
        \u201CThus says the king: \u2018Do you come in peace?\u2019\u2009\u201D Jehu
        replied, \u201CWhat have you to do with peace? Rein in behind me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And the watchman reported, \u201CHe approached them, but he has not
        returned; and the driving [of the chariot] is like that of Jehu the son of
        Nimshi, for he drives furiously.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Joram said, \u201CHarness [the chariot].\u201D When they harnessed
        his chariot horses, Joram king of Israel and Ahaziah king of Judah went out,
        each in his chariot, and they went out to meet Jehu and met him on the property
        of Naboth the Jezreelite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "When Joram saw Jehu, he said, \u201CDo you come in peace, Jehu?\u201D
        And he answered, \u201CWhat peace [can exist] as long as the fornications
        of your mother Jezebel and her sorceries are so many?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So Joram reined [his chariot] around and fled, and he said to Ahaziah,
        \u201CTreachery and betrayal, Ahaziah!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But Jehu drew his bow with his full strength and shot Joram between
        his shoulders; and the arrow went out through his heart and he sank down
        in his chariot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Jehu said to Bidkar his officer, \u201CPick him up and throw
        him on the property of the field of Naboth the Jezreelite; for I remember
        when you and I were riding together after his father Ahab, that the Lord
        uttered this prophecy against him: "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Jehu Assassinates Ahaziah'
      title: Jehu Assassinates Ahaziah
      number: 26
      content: "\u2018I certainly saw the blood of Naboth and the blood of his sons
        yesterday,\u2019 says the Lord, \u2018and I will repay you on this property,\u2019
        says the Lord. Now then, pick him up and throw him into the property [of
        Naboth], in accordance with the word of the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "When Ahaziah the king of Judah saw this, he fled by the way of the
        garden house. Jehu pursued him and said, \u201CShoot him too, [while he is]
        in the chariot.\u201D So they shot him at the ascent to Gur, which is by
        Ibleam. And Ahaziah fled to Megiddo and died there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then his servants carried him in a chariot to Jerusalem and buried
        him in his grave with his fathers in the City of David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'In the eleventh year of Joram, the son of Ahab, Ahaziah became king
        over Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So when Jehu came to Jezreel, Jezebel heard about it, and she painted
        her eyes and adorned her head and looked down from the [upper] window. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "As Jehu entered in at the gate, she said, \u201CIs it well, Zimri,
        your master\u2019s murderer?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: Jezebel Is Killed'
      title: Jezebel Is Killed
      number: 32
      content: "Then Jehu raised his face toward the window and said, \u201CWho is
        on my side? Who?\u201D And two or three officials looked down at him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And he said, \u201CThrow her down.\u201D So they threw her down,
        and some of her blood spattered on the wall and on the horses, and he trampled
        her underfoot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "When he came in, he ate and drank, and said, \u201CSee now to this
        cursed woman and bury her, for she is a king\u2019s daughter.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'They went to bury her, but they found nothing left of her except
        the skull and the feet and the palms of her hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "So they returned and told Jehu. Then he said, \u201CThis is the word
        of the Lord, which He spoke through His servant Elijah the Tishbite, saying,
        \u2018In the property of Jezreel the dogs shall eat the flesh of Jezebel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "The corpse of Jezebel will be like dung on the surface of the field
        in the property of Jezreel, so they cannot say, \u201CThis is Jezebel.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judgment upon Ahab\u2019s House"
      title: "Judgment upon Ahab\u2019s House"
      number: 1
      content: '  Ahab had seventy sons [and grandsons] in Samaria. So Jehu wrote
        letters and sent them to Samaria, to the rulers of Jezreel, to the elders,
        and to the guardians of the children of Ahab, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CNow as soon as this letter comes to you, since your master\u2019s
        sons (male descendants) are with you, as well as chariots and horses and
        a fortified city and weapons, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "select the best and most capable of your master\u2019s sons, and
        set him on his father\u2019s throne, and fight for your master\u2019s [royal]
        house.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But they were extremely afraid and said, \u201CLook, the two kings
        did not stand before Jehu; so how can we stand?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the one who was in charge of the household, and the one who was
        overseer of the city, the elders, and the guardians [of the children] sent
        word to Jehu, saying, \u201CWe are your servants and we will do whatever
        you tell us, but we will not make any man king; do what is good in your eyes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Jehu wrote a second letter to them, saying, \u201CIf you are
        with me and will obey me, take the heads of your master\u2019s sons, and
        come to me at Jezreel tomorrow about this time.\u201D Now the [dead] king\u2019s
        sons, seventy persons, were with the great men of the city, who were rearing
        them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When the letter came to them, they took the king\u2019s sons and
        slaughtered them, seventy persons, and put their heads in baskets, and sent
        them to Jehu at Jezreel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "When a messenger came and told him, \u201CThey have brought the heads
        of the king\u2019s sons,\u201D he said, \u201CPut them in two heaps at the
        entrance of the city gate until morning.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The next morning he went out and stood and said to all the people,
        \u201CYou are just and innocent; behold, I conspired against [Joram] my master
        and killed him, but who killed all these? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Know then [without any doubt] that there shall fall to the earth
        nothing of the word of the Lord, which the Lord spoke concerning the house
        of Ahab, for the Lord has done what He said through His servant Elijah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Jehu killed all who remained of the house of Ahab in Jezreel,
        and all his great men and his familiar friends and his priests, until he
        left him without a survivor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And he set out and went to Samaria. On the way as he was at the place
        of the sand heaps [meeting place] for the shepherds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Jehu met the relatives of Ahaziah king of Judah and said, \u201CWho
        are you?\u201D They answered, \u201CWe are the relatives of Ahaziah; and
        we came down to greet the royal princes and the sons of the queen mother
        [Jezebel].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Jehu said, \u201CTake them alive.\u201D So they took them alive
        and [later] slaughtered them at the well by the place of the sand heaps,
        forty-two men; he left none of them [alive].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When Jehu went on from there, he met Jehonadab the son of Rechab
        coming to meet him. He greeted him and said to him, \u201CIs your heart right,
        as my heart is with yours?\u201D Jehonadab answered, \u201CIt is.\u201D Jehu
        said \u201CIf it is, give me your hand.\u201D He gave him his hand, and Jehu
        pulled him up into the chariot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And he said, \u201CCome with me and see my zeal for the Lord.\u201D
        So he had Jehonadab in his chariot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Jehu Destroys Baal Worshipers'
      title: Jehu Destroys Baal Worshipers
      number: 17
      content: "When Jehu came to Samaria, he killed everyone who remained of Ahab\u2019s
        family in Samaria, until he had destroyed all of them, in accordance with
        the word of the Lord which He spoke to Elijah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Jehu assembled all the people and said [in pretense] to them, \u201CAhab
        served Baal a little; Jehu will serve him much [more]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now, summon unto me all the prophets of Baal, all his worshipers
        and all his priests. Let no one be missing, for I have a great sacrifice
        for Baal; whoever is missing shall not live.\u201D But Jehu did it with trickery,
        in order to destroy the worshipers of Baal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Jehu said, \u201CConsecrate a festive assembly (celebration) for
        Baal.\u201D And they proclaimed it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then Jehu sent throughout Israel, and all the worshipers of Baal
        came; there was no one left who did not come. They went to the house (temple)
        of Baal, and the house of Baal was filled from one end to the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "He said to the man in charge of the wardrobe, \u201CBring out garments
        for all the worshipers of Baal.\u201D And he brought the garments out to
        them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Jehu with Jehonadab the son of Rechab went into the house of
        Baal; and he said to the worshipers of Baal, \u201CSearch carefully and see
        that there are no servants of the Lord here with you, but only the worshipers
        of Baal.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then they went in to offer sacrifices and burnt offerings.  Now Jehu
        had stationed eighty men outside for himself and said, \u201CIf any of the
        men whom I have brought into your hands escape, the one who lets him go shall
        forfeit his own life for that man\u2019s life.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then it came about, as soon as he had finished offering the burnt
        offering, that Jehu said to the guards and to the royal officers, \u201CGo
        in and kill them; let no one come out.\u201D And they killed them with the
        edge of the sword; and the guard and the royal officers threw their bodies
        out, and went to the inner room of the house of Baal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'They brought out the sacred pillars (obelisks) of the house of Baal
        and burned them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'They also tore down the sacred pillar of Baal and tore down the house
        of Baal, and made it into a latrine [forever unclean] to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Thus Jehu eradicated Baal from Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'However, Jehu did not turn from the [idolatrous] sins of Jeroboam
        the son of Nebat, who made Israel sin, that is, [led them to worship] the
        golden calves which were at Bethel and Dan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "The Lord said to Jehu, \u201CBecause you have done well in executing
        what is right in My eyes, and have done to the house of Ahab in accordance
        with everything that was in My heart, your sons (descendants) shall sit on
        Israel\u2019s throne to the fourth generation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'But Jehu did not take care to walk in the law of the Lord, the God
        of Israel, with all his heart; he did not turn from the sins of Jeroboam,
        who made Israel sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '  So in those days the Lord began to cut off portions of Israel;
        Hazael [of Aram] defeated them throughout the territory of Israel: '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: Jehoahaz Succeeds Jehu'
      title: Jehoahaz Succeeds Jehu
      number: 33
      content: 'from the Jordan eastward, all the land of Gilead, the Gadites and
        the Reubenites and the Manassites, from Aroer, which is by the Arnon River,
        even Gilead and Bashan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehu and everything that he did and all
        his might, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings
        of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Jehu slept with his fathers [in death], and they buried him in Samaria.
        Jehoahaz his son became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: The time that Jehu reigned over Israel in Samaria was twenty-eight
        years.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Athaliah Queen of Judah'
      title: Athaliah Queen of Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  When Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah [king of Judah] saw that her
        son was dead, she arose and destroyed all the royal offspring. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But Jehosheba, the daughter of King Joram [of Judah and half] sister
        of Ahaziah, took Joash the son of Ahaziah and abducted him from among the
        king\u2019s sons who were to be killed, and hid him and his nurse in the
        bedroom. So they hid him from Athaliah, and he was not put to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Joash was hidden with his nurse in the house (temple) of the Lord
        for six years, while Athaliah reigned over the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Now in the seventh year Jehoiada [the priest, Jehosheba\u2019s husband]
        sent for the captains of hundreds of the Carites and of the guard and brought
        them to him to the house of the Lord. Then he made a covenant with them and
        put them under oath in the house of the Lord, and showed them the king\u2019s
        [hidden] son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He commanded them, saying, \u201CThis is the thing that you shall
        do: a third of you who come in [reporting for duty] on the Sabbath shall
        keep watch over the king\u2019s house "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '(a third shall also be at the [city] gate Sur, and a third at the
        gate behind the guards); so you shall keep watch over the palace [from three
        posts] for defense. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Two units of you, all those who go out [off duty] on the Sabbath,
        shall also keep watch over the house (temple) of the Lord for [the protection
        of] the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You shall surround the [young] king, each man with weapons in his
        hand; and whoever comes through the ranks shall be put to death. You are
        to be with the king when he goes out and when he comes in.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The captains of hundreds acted in accordance with everything that
        Jehoiada the priest commanded; and each of them took his men who were to
        come in (on duty) on the Sabbath, with those who were to go out (off duty)
        on the Sabbath, and they came to Jehoiada the priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The priest gave to the captains of hundreds the spears and shields
        that had been King David\u2019s, which were in the house of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the guards stood, each man with weapons in his hand, from the
        right side to the left side of the temple area, by the altar [in the courtyard]
        and by the temple [proper], all around the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Jehoiada brought out the king\u2019s son and put the crown on
        him and gave him the Testimony [a copy of the Mosaic Law]; and they made
        him king and anointed him, and they clapped their hands and said, \u201CLong
        live the king!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When Athaliah heard the sound of the guards and of the people, she
        went into the house of the Lord to the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When she looked, behold, there stood the [young] king [on the platform]
        by the pillar, as was customary [on such occasions], and the captains and
        the trumpeters were beside the king; and all the people of the land rejoicing
        and blowing the trumpets. Then Athaliah tore her clothes and cried, \u201CTreason!
        Treason!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Jehoiada the priest commanded the captains of hundreds appointed
        over the army and said to them, \u201CTake her out between the ranks, and
        whoever follows her put to death with the sword.\u201D For the priest had
        said, \u201CLet her not be put to death in the house (temple) of the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So they seized her, and she went through the horses\u2019 entrance
        to the king\u2019s house (palace), and she was put to death there.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Jehoiada made a covenant between the Lord, the king, and the
        people, that they would be the Lord\u2019s people\u2014also between the king
        and the people [to be his subjects]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then all the people of the land went to the house of Baal and tore
        it down. They utterly smashed his altar and his images to pieces, and they
        put Mattan the priest of Baal to death in front of the altars. And [Jehoiada]
        the priest appointed officers over the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then he took the captains of hundreds, the Carites (royal bodyguards),
        the guard, and all the people of the land; and they brought the [young] king
        down from the house of the Lord, and came by way of the guards\u2019 gate
        to the king\u2019s house. And [little] Joash sat on the throne of the kings. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So all the people of the land rejoiced and the city [of Jerusalem]
        was quiet. For they had put Athaliah to death with the sword at the king\u2019s
        house.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Jehoash (Joash) was seven years old when he became king.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joash (Jehoash) Reigns over Judah'
      title: Joash (Jehoash) Reigns over Judah
      number: 1
      content: "  In the seventh year of Jehu [king of Israel], Jehoash became king
        [over Judah], and he reigned forty years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s
        name was Zibiah of Beersheba. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Jehoash did right in the sight of the Lord all his days in which
        Jehoiada the priest instructed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Temple to Be Repaired'
      title: The Temple to Be Repaired
      number: 3
      content: 'Only the high places were not removed; the people were still sacrificing
        and burning incense [to the Lord] on the high places [rather than at the
        temple].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jehoash said to the priests, \u201CAll the money for the dedicated
        things which is brought into the house of the Lord, in current money, both
        the money of each man\u2019s assessment [for all those bound by vows], and
        all the money which any man\u2019s heart prompts him to bring into the house
        (temple) of the Lord, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "let the priests receive such contributions for themselves, each from
        his acquaintance; and they shall repair any breach in the house of the Lord,
        wherever a breach is found.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But it came about in the twenty-third year of [the reign of] King
        Jehoash, that the priests still had not repaired the damages of the Lord\u2019s
        house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then King Jehoash called for Jehoiada the priest and the [other]
        priests and said to them, \u201CWhy are you not repairing the damage of the
        house (temple)? Now then, do not take any more money from your acquaintances,
        but turn it all over for [the repair of] the damages of the house.\u201D
        [You are no longer responsible for this work. I will take it into my own
        hands.] "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the priests agreed that they would receive no [more] money from
        the people, nor [be responsible to] repair the damages of the house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Jehoiada the priest took a chest and bored a hole in its lid
        and set it beside the altar, on the right side as one enters the house of
        the Lord; and the priests who guarded the door put in the chest all the money
        that was brought [by the people] into the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And whenever they saw that there was a large amount of money in the
        chest, the king\u2019s scribe and the high priest came up and tied it in
        bags and counted the money that was found in the house of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then they gave the money, which was weighed out into the hands of
        those who were doing the work, who had the oversight of the house of the
        Lord; and they paid it out to the carpenters and builders who worked on the
        house (temple) of the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and to the masons and stonecutters, and to buy timber and hewn (cut)
        stone to repair any breach in the house of the Lord, and for all that was
        laid out for repairing the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'However, there were not made for the house of the Lord basins of
        silver, snuffers, bowls, trumpets, any gold containers or [other] silver
        containers, from the money that was brought into the house of the Lord; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'but they gave that to those who did the work, and with it they repaired
        the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Moreover, they did not require an accounting from the men into whose
        hands they placed the money to be paid to those who did the work, for they
        acted in good faith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Money from the guilt offerings and money from the sin offerings was
        not brought into the house of the Lord [for repairs]; it was for the priests.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Hazael king of Aram (Syria) went up, fought against Gath [in
        Philistia], and captured it. And Hazael resolved to go up to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Joash (Jehoash) Succeeded by Amaziah in Judah'
      title: Joash (Jehoash) Succeeded by Amaziah in Judah
      number: 18
      content: "So Jehoash the king of Judah took all the sacred things that Jehoshaphat
        and Jehoram and Ahaziah, his fathers, kings of Judah, had dedicated, and
        his own sacred things and all the gold that was found in the treasuries of
        the house (temple) of the Lord and of the king\u2019s house, and sent them
        to Hazael king of Aram; and Hazael departed from Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Joash and everything that he did, are
        they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'His servants arose and formed a conspiracy [against him] and struck
        down Joash [in revenge] at the house of Millo, [on the way] that goes down
        to Silla. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: For Jozacar (Jozachar) the son of Shimeath and Jehozabad the son of
        Shomer, his servants, struck him and he died; and they buried Joash with
        his fathers in the City of David. Amaziah his son became king in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Kings of Israel: Jehoahaz and Joash (Jehoash)'
      title: 'Kings of Israel: Jehoahaz and Joash (Jehoash)'
      number: 1
      content: '  In the twenty-third year of Joash the son of Ahaziah, king of Judah,
        Jehoahaz the son of Jehu became king over Israel in Samaria, and he reigned
        seventeen years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord, and followed the [idolatrous]
        sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who made Israel sin; he did not turn from
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So the anger of the Lord was kindled and burned against Israel, and
        He handed them over time and again to Hazael the king of Aram (Syria), and
        of Ben-hadad the son of Hazael. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Jehoahaz sought the favor of the Lord, and the Lord listened
        to him; for He saw the oppression of Israel, how the king of Aram oppressed
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the Lord gave Israel a savior [to rescue them and give them
        peace], so that they escaped from under the hand of the Arameans; and the
        sons (descendants) of Israel lived in their tents as before. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Yet they did not turn from the [idolatrous] sins of the [royal] house
        of Jeroboam, who made Israel sin; but walked in them. And the Asherah [set
        up by Ahab] also remained standing in Samaria [Israel\u2019s capital]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For he left to Jehoahaz [king of Israel] an army of no more than
        fifty horsemen, ten chariots, and 10,000 footmen, for the king of Aram (Ben-hadad)
        had destroyed them and made them like dust to be trampled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoahaz, everything that he did and
        his might, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings
        of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Jehoahaz slept with his fathers [in death], and they buried him in
        Samaria; Joash his son became king in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In the thirty-seventh year of Joash king of Judah, Jehoash (Joash)
        the son of Jehoahaz became king over Israel in Samaria, and reigned sixteen
        years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord; he did not turn away from all
        the [idolatrous] sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who made Israel sin;
        but he walked in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Joash, everything that he did, and his
        might with which he fought against Amaziah king of Judah, are they not written
        in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Death of Elisha'
      title: Death of Elisha
      number: 13
      content: 'Joash slept with his fathers [in death], and Jeroboam [II] sat on
        his throne. Joash was buried in Samaria with the kings of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now Elisha had become sick with the illness by which he would die.
        And Joash the king of Israel came down to him and wept over him and said,
        \u201CO my father, my father, the chariot of Israel and its horsemen!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Elisha said to him, \u201CTake a bow and arrows.\u201D So he
        took a bow and arrows. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then he said to the king of Israel, \u201CPut your hand on the bow.\u201D
        And he put his hand on it, and Elisha put his hands on the king\u2019s hands. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said, \u201COpen the window to the east,\u201D and he opened
        it. Then Elisha said, \u201CShoot!\u201D And he shot. And Elisha said, \u201CThe
        Lord\u2019s arrow of victory, the arrow of victory over Aram (Syria); for
        you will strike the Arameans in Aphek until you have destroyed them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then he said, \u201CTake the arrows,\u201D and he took them. And
        Elisha said to the king of Israel, \u201CStrike the ground,\u201D and he
        struck it three times and stopped. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So the man of God was angry with him and said, \u201CYou should have
        struck five or six times; then you would have struck down Aram until you
        had destroyed it. But now you shall strike Aram only three times.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Elisha died, and they buried him. Now marauding bands of Moabites
        would invade the land in the spring of the year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And it happened that as a man was being buried [on an open bier],
        they saw a marauding band [coming]; and they threw the man into Elisha\u2019s
        grave. But when the [body of the] man [was being let down and] touched the
        bones of Elisha he revived and stood up on his feet.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Hazael the king of Aram oppressed Israel all the days of Jehoahaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But the Lord was gracious to them and had compassion on them and
        turned toward them for the sake of His covenant with Abraham, Isaac, and
        Jacob, and He was unwilling to destroy them, and did not cast them from His
        presence until now.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Hazael king of Aram (Syria) died; Ben-hadad his son became king in
        his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Then Jehoash (Joash) the son of Jehoahaz recovered from Ben-hadad
        the son of Hazael the cities which he had taken from Jehoahaz his father
        by war. Three times Joash defeated Ben-hadad and recovered the cities of
        Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Amaziah Reigns over Judah'
      title: Amaziah Reigns over Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  In the second year of Joash the son of Jehoahaz, king of Israel,
        Amaziah the son of Joash king of Judah became king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jehoaddin of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He did right in the sight of the Lord, though not like David his
        father (ancestor). He acted in accordance with everything that his father
        Joash had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'However, the high places were not removed; the people were still
        sacrificing and burning incense on the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "As soon as the kingdom was firmly in Amaziah\u2019s hand, he executed
        his servants who had killed his father the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But he did not put the sons of the murderers to death, in compliance
        with what is written in the Book of the Law of Moses, in which the Lord commanded,
        saying, \u201CThe fathers shall not be put to death for the sons, nor shall
        the sons be put to death for the fathers; but each shall be put to death
        [only] for his own sin.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Amaziah killed 10,000 [men] of Edom in the Valley of Salt, and took
        Sela (rock) by war, and renamed it Joktheel, to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Amaziah sent messengers to Jehoash (Joash) the son of Jehoahaz,
        the son of Jehu, king of Israel, saying, \u201CCome, let us face each other
        [in combat].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jehoash the king of Israel sent word to Amaziah king of Judah, saying,
        \u201CThe [little] thorn-bush in Lebanon sent word to the [tall] cedar in
        Lebanon, saying, \u2018Give your daughter to my son as wife.\u2019 But a
        wild beast that was in Lebanon passed by and trampled the thorn-bush. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You have indeed defeated Edom, and your heart has lifted you up [in
        pride]. Enjoy your glory but stay at home; for why should you plunge into
        misery so that you, even you, would fall [at my hand], and Judah with you?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But Amaziah would not listen. So Jehoash king of Israel went up;
        and he and Amaziah king of Judah faced each other [in combat] at Beth-shemesh,
        which belongs to Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Judah was defeated by Israel, and every man fled to his tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Jehoash king of Israel captured Amaziah the king of Judah, the
        son of Jehoash (Joash), the son of Ahaziah, at Beth-shemesh, and came to
        Jerusalem and broke through the wall of Jerusalem from the Gate of Ephraim
        to the Corner Gate, 400 cubits (600 feet). '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Jeroboam II Succeeds Jehoash (Joash) in Israel'
      title: Jeroboam II Succeeds Jehoash (Joash) in Israel
      number: 14
      content: "He seized all the gold and silver and all the utensils found in the
        house (temple) of the Lord and in the treasuries of the king\u2019s house,
        as well as hostages, and returned to Samaria.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoash which he did, and his might and
        how he fought with Amaziah the king of Judah, are they not written in the
        Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Azariah (Uzziah) Succeeds Amaziah in Judah'
      title: Azariah (Uzziah) Succeeds Amaziah in Judah
      number: 16
      content: 'Jehoash slept with his fathers [in death] and was buried in Samaria
        with the kings of Israel. His son Jeroboam [II] became king in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Amaziah the son of Joash king of Judah lived for fifteen years after
        the death of Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The rest of the acts of Amaziah, are they not written in the Book
        of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now a conspiracy was formed against him in Jerusalem, and Amaziah
        fled [south] to Lachish; but they sent [men] after him to Lachish and killed
        him there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then they carried him on horses and he was buried at Jerusalem with
        his fathers in the City of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And all the people of Judah took Azariah, who was [only] sixteen
        years old, and made him king in place of his father Amaziah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He built Elath and restored it to Judah after the king [his father
        Amaziah] slept with his fathers [in death].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In the fifteenth year of Amaziah the son of Joash king of Judah,
        Jeroboam [II] the son of Joash (Jehoash) king of Israel became king in Samaria,
        and reigned forty-one years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord; he did not turn from all the
        [idolatrous] sins of Jeroboam [I] the son of Nebat, who made Israel sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jeroboam restored Israel\u2019s border from the entrance of Hamath
        to the Sea of the Arabah (Dead Sea), in accordance with the word of the Lord,
        the God of Israel, which He spoke through His servant Jonah the son of Amittai,
        the prophet who was from Gath-hepher. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For the Lord saw the affliction (suffering) of Israel as very bitter;
        there was no one left, bond or free, nor any helper for Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Zechariah Reigns over Israel'
      title: Zechariah Reigns over Israel
      number: 27
      content: 'But the Lord had not said that He would blot out the name of Israel
        from under the heavens, so He saved them by the hand of Jeroboam [II] the
        son of Joash [king of Israel].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The rest of the acts of Jeroboam [II], all that he did, his might,
        how he fought, and how he recovered Damascus and Hamath for Israel, which
        had belonged to Judah, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles
        of the Kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Jeroboam [II] slept with his fathers [in death], even with the kings
        of Israel. Zechariah his son became king in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Series of Kings: Azariah (Uzziah) over Judah'
      title: 'Series of Kings: Azariah (Uzziah) over Judah'
      number: 1
      content: '  In the twenty-seventh year of Jeroboam [II] king of Israel, Azariah
        (Uzziah) the son of Amaziah king of Judah became king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He was sixteen years old when he became king, and he reigned fifty-two
        years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jecoliah of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He did right in the sight of the Lord, in accordance with all that
        his father Amaziah had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Only [the altars on] the high places were not removed; the people
        still sacrificed and burned incense on the high places [instead of worshiping
        God at the temple]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the Lord struck (afflicted) the king, and he was a leper until
        the day of his death, and lived in a separate house. Jotham the king\u2019s
        son was in charge of the household, judging the people of the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now the rest of Azariah\u2019s acts, and everything that he did,
        are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Zechariah over Israel'
      title: Zechariah over Israel
      number: 7
      content: 'Azariah slept with his fathers [in death], and they buried him with
        his fathers in the City of David. His son Jotham became king in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the thirty-eighth year of Azariah king of Judah, Zechariah the
        son of Jeroboam [II] became king over Israel in Samaria for six months. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord, just as his fathers had done;
        he did not turn from the sins of Jeroboam [I] the son of Nebat, who made
        Israel sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But Shallum the son of Jabesh conspired against Zechariah and struck
        and killed him in the presence of the people and reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Zechariah, behold, they are written in
        the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "This is [the fulfillment of] the word of the Lord which He spoke
        to Jehu, saying, \u201CYour sons (descendants) shall sit on the throne of
        Israel to the fourth generation.\u201D And so it came to pass.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Shallum the son of Jabesh became king in the thirty-ninth year of
        Uzziah (Azariah) king of Judah, and he reigned one month in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For Menahem the son of Gadi went up from Tirzah and came to Samaria,
        and struck and killed Shallum the son of Jabesh in Samaria and became king
        in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The rest of Shallum\u2019s acts, and his conspiracy which he made,
        they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Menahem over Israel'
      title: Menahem over Israel
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Menahem struck [the town of] Tiphsah and all who were in it
        and its borders from Tirzah; [he attacked it] because they did not surrender
        to him; so he struck it and ripped up all the women there who were pregnant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'In the thirty-ninth year of Azariah king of Judah, Menahem the son
        of Gadi became king over Israel, and reigned ten years in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord; for all his days he did not
        turn from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who caused Israel to sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Pul, [Tiglath-pileser III] king of Assyria, came against the land
        [of Israel], and Menahem gave Pul a thousand talents of silver [as a bribe],
        so that he might help him to strengthen his control of the kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Menahem exacted the money from Israel, from all the wealthy, influential
        men, fifty shekels of silver from each man to give to the king of Assyria.
        So the king of Assyria turned back and did not stay there in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now the rest of Menahem\u2019s acts, and everything that he did,
        are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel? "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Pekahiah over Israel'
      title: Pekahiah over Israel
      number: 22
      content: 'And Menahem slept with his fathers [in death]; his son Pekahiah became
        king in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In the fiftieth year of Azariah king of Judah, Pekahiah the son of
        Menahem became king over Israel, and reigned two years in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord; he did not turn from the [idolatrous]
        sins of Jeroboam [I] the son of Nebat, who made Israel sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But Pekah the son of Remaliah, his officer, conspired against Pekahiah
        and struck him in Samaria, in the citadel of the king\u2019s house, with
        Argob and Arieh; and with Pekah were fifty Gileadites. So he killed Pekahiah
        and became king in his place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Pekah over Israel'
      title: Pekah over Israel
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Pekahiah, all that he did, they are written
        in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'In the fifty-second year of Azariah king of Judah, Pekah the son
        of Remaliah became king over Israel, and reigned twenty years in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord; he did not turn from the [idolatrous]
        sins of Jeroboam [I] the son of Nebat, who made Israel sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'In the days of Pekah king of Israel, Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria
        came and took Ijon, Abel-beth-maacah, Janoah, Kedesh, Hazor, Gilead, and
        Galilee, all the land of [the tribe of] Naphtali, and he carried the people
        captive to Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Hoshea the son of Elah conspired against Pekah the son of Remaliah
        [of Israel]; he struck and killed him, and became king in his place in the
        twentieth year of Jotham the son of Uzziah [king of Judah]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: Jotham over Judah'
      title: Jotham over Judah
      number: 31
      content: "Now the rest of Pekah\u2019s acts, and everything that he did, they
        are written in the Book of the Chronicles of Israel\u2019s Kings.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'In the second year of Pekah the son of Remaliah king of Israel, Jotham
        the son of Uzziah king of Judah became king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "When he was twenty-five years old, he became king [over Judah], and
        he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jerusha
        daughter of Zadok. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'He did what was right in the sight of the Lord, in accordance with
        everything that his father Uzziah had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Only [the altars on] the high places were not removed; the people
        still sacrificed and burned incense on the high places [rather than in the
        temple]. He built the upper gate of the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Now the rest of the acts of Jotham, and all that he did, are they
        not written in the Book of the Chronicles of Judah\u2019s Kings? "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "In those days the Lord began sending Rezin the king of Aram (Syria)
        and [Israel\u2019s king] Pekah the son of Remaliah against Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: Jotham slept with his fathers [in death], and was buried with them
        in the City of David his father (ancestor). Ahaz his son became king in his
        place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ahaz Reigns over Judah'
      title: Ahaz Reigns over Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  In the seventeenth year of Pekah the son of Remaliah, Ahaz the
        son of Jotham, king of Judah, became king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Ahaz was twenty years old when he became king, and he reigned sixteen
        years in Jerusalem. He did not do what was right in the sight of the Lord
        his God, as his father (ancestor) David had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Instead he walked in the way of the [idolatrous] kings of Israel,
        and even made his son pass through the fire [as a human sacrifice], in accordance
        with the repulsive [and idolatrous] practices of the [pagan] nations whom
        the Lord drove out before the Israelites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He also sacrificed and burned incense on the high places and on the
        hills and under every green tree.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Rezin the king of Aram (Syria) and Pekah the son of Remaliah,
        king of Israel, came up to Jerusalem to wage war. They besieged Ahaz, but
        could not overcome and conquer him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Ahaz Seeks Help of Assyria'
      title: Ahaz Seeks Help of Assyria
      number: 6
      content: 'At that time Rezin king of Aram recovered Elath [in Edom] for Aram,
        and drove the Jews away from it. The Arameans came to Elath, and live there
        to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Ahaz sent messengers to Tiglath-pileser king of Assyria, saying,
        \u201CI am your servant and son. Come up and rescue me from the hand of the
        kings of Aram and of Israel, who are rising up against me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Ahaz took the silver and gold that was found in the house of
        the Lord and in the treasuries of the king\u2019s house, and sent a gift
        to the king of Assyria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Damascus Falls'
      title: Damascus Falls
      number: 9
      content: 'So the king of Assyria listened to him; and he went up against Damascus
        and captured it, and carried its people away into exile to Kir, and put Rezin
        [king of Aram] to death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now King Ahaz went to Damascus to meet Tiglath-pileser the king of
        Assyria, and saw the pagan altar which was at Damascus. Then King Ahaz sent
        a model of the altar to Urijah the priest along with a [detailed] pattern
        for all its construction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Urijah the priest built an altar; in accordance with everything
        that King Ahaz had sent from Damascus, that is how Urijah the priest made
        it before King Ahaz returned from Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When the king came from Damascus, he saw the altar; then the king
        approached the altar and offered [sacrifices] on it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and burned his burnt offering and his grain offering, and poured
        out his drink offering, and sprinkled the blood of his peace offerings on
        the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He brought the bronze altar, which was before the Lord, from the
        front of the house (temple), from between the [new] altar and the house of
        the Lord, and put it on the north side of the [new] altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then King Ahaz commanded Urijah the priest, saying, \u201CUpon the
        great [new] altar, burn the morning burnt offering and the evening grain
        offering, and the king\u2019s burnt offering and his grain offering, with
        the burnt offering of all the people of the land and their grain offering
        and their drink offerings; and sprinkle on the new altar all the blood of
        the burnt offering and all the blood of the sacrifice. But the [old] bronze
        altar shall be kept for me to use to examine the sacrifices.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Urijah the priest acted in accordance with everything that King Ahaz
        commanded.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then King Ahaz cut away the frames of the basin stands [in the temple],
        and removed the basin from [each of] them; and he took down the [large] Sea
        from the bronze oxen which were under it, and put it on a plastered stone
        floor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Hezekiah Reigns over Judah'
      title: Hezekiah Reigns over Judah
      number: 18
      content: 'He removed from the house of the Lord the covered way for the Sabbath
        which they had built in the house, and the outer entrance of the king, because
        of the king of Assyria [who might confiscate them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Ahaz, are they not written in the Book
        of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: So Ahaz slept with his fathers [in death] and was buried with his
        fathers in the City of David; and his son Hezekiah became king in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hoshea Reigns over Israel'
      title: Hoshea Reigns over Israel
      number: 1
      content: '  In the twelfth year of Ahaz king of Judah, Hoshea the son of Elah
        became king over Israel in Samaria, and reigned for nine years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord, but not as the kings of Israel
        who came before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Shalmaneser [V] king of Assyria came up against him, and Hoshea became
        his servant and paid him tribute (money). '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But the king of Assyria discovered a conspiracy in Hoshea, who sent
        messengers to So, king of Egypt, and offered no tribute to the king of Assyria,
        as he had done year by year; therefore the king of Assyria arrested him and
        bound him in prison.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Israel Captive'
      title: Israel Captive
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the king of Assyria invaded all the land [of Israel] and went
        up to Samaria and besieged it for three years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Why Israel Fell'
      title: Why Israel Fell
      number: 6
      content: 'In the ninth year of Hoshea, the king of Assyria took Samaria and
        carried [the people of] Israel into exile to Assyria, and settled them in
        Halah and in Habor, by the river of Gozan, and in the cities of the Medes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now this came about because the Israelites had sinned against the
        Lord their God, who had brought them up from the land of Egypt, from under
        the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt; and they had feared [and worshiped] other
        gods '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and walked in the customs of the [pagan] nations whom the Lord had
        driven out before the sons (descendants) of Israel, and in the pagan customs
        of the kings of Israel which they had introduced. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Israelites ascribed things to the Lord their God which were not
        true. They built for themselves high places [of worship] in all their towns,
        from [the lonely] lookout tower to the [populous] fortified city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They set up for themselves sacred pillars (memorial stones) and Asherim
        on every high hill and under every green tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'There they burned incense on all the high places, just as the [pagan]
        nations whom the Lord had deported before them; and they did evil and contemptible
        things, provoking the Lord [to anger]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And they served idols, of which the Lord had said to them, \u201CYou
        shall not do this thing.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Yet the Lord warned Israel and Judah through all His prophets and
        every seer, saying, \u201CTurn from your evil ways and keep My commandments
        and My statutes, in accordance with all the Law which I commanded your fathers,
        and which I sent to you by My servants the prophets.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'However they did not listen, but stiffened their necks as did their
        fathers who did not believe (trust in, rely on, remain steadfast to) the
        Lord their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They rejected His statutes and His covenant which He made with their
        fathers, as well as His warnings that he gave them. And they followed vanity
        [that is, false gods, idols] and became vain (empty-headed). They followed
        the [pagan practices of the] nations which surrounded them, although the
        Lord had commanded that they were not to do as they did. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They abandoned all the commandments of the Lord their God and made
        for themselves cast images of two calves; and they made an Asherah [idol]
        and worshiped all the [starry] host of heaven and served Baal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They made their sons and their daughters pass through the fire [as
        human sacrifices], and used divination [to foretell the future] and enchantments;
        and they sold themselves to do evil in the sight of the Lord, provoking Him
        to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Therefore the Lord was very angry with Israel and removed them from
        His sight; none [of the tribes] was left except the tribe of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Judah did not keep the commandments of the Lord their God either,
        but walked in the customs which Israel introduced. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So the Lord rejected all the descendants of Israel (Jacob) and [repeatedly]
        afflicted them and handed them over to plunderers, until He had cast them
        out of His sight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When He had torn Israel from the [royal] house of David, they made
        Jeroboam the son of Nebat king. And Jeroboam drove Israel away from following
        the Lord and made them commit a great sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For the Israelites walked in all the [idolatrous] sins which Jeroboam
        committed; they did not turn from them '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Cities of Israel Filled with Strangers'
      title: Cities of Israel Filled with Strangers
      number: 23
      content: 'until the Lord removed Israel from His sight, just as He had foretold
        through all His servants the prophets. So Israel went into exile from their
        own land to Assyria to this day [the date of this writing].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The king of Assyria brought men from Babylon and from Cuthah and
        from Avva and from Hamath and Sepharvaim, and settled them in the cities
        of Samaria in place of the sons (people) of Israel. They took possession
        of Samaria and lived in its cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now when they began to live there, they did not fear the Lord; therefore
        the Lord sent lions among them which killed some of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So the king of Assyria was told, \u201CThe nations whom you have
        sent into exile and settled in the cities of Samaria do not know the custom
        of the god of the land; so He has sent lions among them, and they are killing
        them because they do not know the manner of [worship demanded by] the god
        of the land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then the king of Assyria commanded, \u201CTake back [to Samaria]
        one of the priests whom you brought from there, and have him go and live
        there; and have him teach the people the custom of the god of the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So one of the priests whom they had exiled from Samaria came [back]
        and lived in Bethel and taught them how they should fear [and worship] the
        Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'But every nation still made gods of its own and put them in the houses
        (shrines) of the high places which the Samaritans had made, every nation
        in the cities where they lived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The men of Babylon made Succoth-benoth, the men of Cuth made Nergal,
        the men of Hamath made Ashima, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'the Avvites made Nibhaz and Tartak; and the Sepharvites burned their
        children in the fire to Adrammelech and Anammelech, the gods of Sepharvaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'They also feared the Lord and appointed from among themselves priests
        of the high places, who sacrificed for them in the houses of the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'They feared the Lord, yet served their own gods, following the custom
        of the nations from among whom they had been sent into exile.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'To this day they act in accordance with their former [pagan] customs:
        they do not [really] fear the Lord, nor do they obey their statutes and ordinances,
        nor the law, nor the commandments which the Lord commanded the sons (descendants)
        of Jacob, whom He named Israel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "with whom the Lord had made a covenant and commanded them, saying,
        \u201CYou shall not fear other gods or bow yourselves to them nor serve them,
        nor sacrifice to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'But the Lord, who brought you up from the land of Egypt with great
        power and an outstretched arm, Him you shall fear, and to Him you shall bow
        yourselves down, and to Him you shall sacrifice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'The statutes and the ordinances and the law and the commandment which
        He wrote for you [by the hand of Moses], you shall observe and do forever.
        You shall not fear (worship, serve) other gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'The covenant that I have made with you, you shall not forget; you
        shall not fear other gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "But the Lord your God you shall fear [and worship]; then He will
        rescue you from the hands of all your enemies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'However, they did not listen, but they acted in accordance with their
        former custom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "So these nations [superficially] feared the Lord; they also served
        their idols, as did their children and their children\u2019s children, just
        as their fathers did, so do they to this day [the date of this writing]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hezekiah Reigns over Judah'
      title: Hezekiah Reigns over Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  Now it came about in the third year of Hoshea the son of Elah king
        of Israel, Hezekiah the son of Ahaz king of Judah became king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Abi the daughter
        of Zechariah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Hezekiah did right in the sight of the Lord, in accordance with everything
        that David his father (ancestor) had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He removed the high places [of pagan worship], broke down the images
        (memorial stones) and cut down the Asherim. He also crushed to pieces the
        bronze serpent that Moses had made, for until those days the Israelites had
        burned incense to it; and it was called Nehushtan [a bronze sculpture]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Hezekiah trusted in and relied confidently on the Lord, the God of
        Israel; so that after him there was no one like him among all the kings of
        Judah, nor among those who were before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Hezekiah Victorious'
      title: Hezekiah Victorious
      number: 6
      content: 'For he clung to the Lord; he did not turn away from [faithfully]
        following Him, but he kept His commandments, which the Lord had commanded
        Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the Lord was with Hezekiah; he was successful wherever he went.
        And he rebelled against the king of Assyria and refused to serve him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He defeated the Philistines as far as Gaza [the most distant city]
        and its borders, from the [isolated] lookout tower to the [populous] fortified
        city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now in the fourth year of King Hezekiah, which was the seventh of
        Hoshea the son of Elah king of Israel, Shalmaneser the king of Assyria went
        up against Samaria and besieged it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'At the end of three years they captured it; in the sixth year of
        Hezekiah, which was the ninth year of Hoshea the king of Israel, Samaria
        was taken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the king of Assyria sent Israel into exile to Assyria, and put
        them in Halah, and on the Habor, the river of [the city of] Gozan, and in
        the cities of the Medes, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Invasion of Judah'
      title: Invasion of Judah
      number: 12
      content: 'because they did not obey the voice of the Lord their God, but broke
        His covenant, everything that Moses the servant of the Lord had commanded;
        and they would not listen nor do it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'In the fourteenth year of King Hezekiah, Sennacherib king of Assyria
        went up against all the fortified cities of Judah [except Jerusalem] and
        captured them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Hezekiah king of Judah sent word to the king of Assyria at Lachish,
        saying, \u201CI have done wrong. Withdraw from me; whatever you impose on
        me I will bear.\u201D So the king of Assyria imposed on Hezekiah king of
        Judah [a tribute tax of] three hundred talents of silver and thirty talents
        of gold. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Hezekiah gave him all the silver that was found in the house (temple)
        of the Lord, and in the treasuries of the king\u2019s house (palace). "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'At that time Hezekiah cut away the gold framework from the doors
        of the temple of the Lord and from the doorposts which he had overlaid, and
        gave it to the king of Assyria.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then the king of Assyria sent the Tartan and the Rab-saris and the
        Rabshakeh [his highest officials] with a large army, from Lachish to King
        Hezekiah at Jerusalem. They went up and came to Jerusalem, and when they
        went up and arrived, they stood by the aqueduct of the upper pool, which
        is on the road of the Fuller\u2019s Field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When they called for the king, Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was
        in charge of the [king\u2019s] household, and Shebna the scribe, and Joah
        the son of Asaph the secretary went out to [meet] them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the Rabshakeh said to them, \u201CSay to Hezekiah, \u2018Thus
        says the great king, the king of Assyria, \u201CWhat is [the reason for]
        this confidence that you have? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "You say (but they are only empty words) \u2018I have counsel and
        strength for the war.\u2019 Now on whom do you rely, that you have rebelled
        against me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now pay attention: you are relying on Egypt, on that staff of crushed
        reed; if a man leans on it, it will only go into his hand and pierce it.
        So is Pharaoh king of Egypt to all who trust and rely on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But if you tell me, \u2018We trust in and rely on the Lord our God,\u2019
        is it not He whose high places and altars Hezekiah has removed, and has said
        to Judah and Jerusalem, \u2018You shall worship [only] before this altar
        in Jerusalem\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now then, make a bargain with my lord the king of Assyria, and I
        will give you two thousand horses, if on your part you can put riders on
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "How then can you drive back even one official of the least of my
        master\u2019s servants, when you rely on Egypt for chariots and horsemen? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now have I come up against this place to destroy it without the Lord\u2019s
        approval? The Lord said to me, \u2018Go up against this land and destroy
        it.\u2019\u2009\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, and Shebna and Joah, said to the
        Rabshakeh, \u201CPlease speak to your servants in the Aramaic (Syrian) language,
        because we understand it; and do not speak with us in the Judean (Hebrew)
        language in the hearing of the people who are on the wall.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But the Rabshakeh said to them, \u201CHas my master sent me only
        to your master and to you to say these things? Has he not sent me to the
        men who sit on the wall, [who are doomed by the siege] to eat their own excrement
        and drink their own urine along with you?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then the Rabshakeh stood and shouted out with a loud voice in Judean
        (Hebrew), \u201CHear the word of the great king, the king of Assyria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Thus says the king, \u2018Do not let Hezekiah deceive you, for he
        will not be able to rescue you from my hand; "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "nor let Hezekiah make you trust in and rely on the Lord, saying,
        \u201CThe Lord will certainly rescue us, and this city [of Jerusalem] will
        not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Do not listen to Hezekiah, for thus says the king of Assyria: \u201CSurrender
        to me and come out to [meet] me, and every man may eat from his own vine
        and fig tree, and every man may drink the waters of his own well, "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "until I come and take you away to a land like your own land, a land
        of grain and new wine, a land of bread and vineyards, a land of olive trees
        and honey, so that you may live and not die.\u201D Do not listen to Hezekiah
        when he misleads and incites you, saying, \u201CThe Lord will rescue us!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Has any one of the gods of the nations ever rescued his land from
        the hand of the king of Assyria? '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Where are the gods of Hamath and Arpad [in Aram]? Where are the gods
        of Sepharvaim, Hena, and Ivvah [in the valley of the Euphrates]? Have they
        rescued Samaria (Israel\u2019s capital) from my hand? "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Who among all the gods of the lands have rescued their lands from
        my hand, that the Lord would rescue Jerusalem from my hand?\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "But the people kept silent and did not answer him, for the king had
        commanded, \u201CDo not answer him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was in charge of the [royal]
        household, and Shebna the scribe and Joah the son of Asaph the secretary,
        came to Hezekiah with their clothes torn [in grief and despair] and told
        him what the Rabshakeh had said.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Isaiah Encourages Hezekiah'
      title: Isaiah Encourages Hezekiah
      number: 1
      content: '  When king Hezekiah heard it, he tore his clothes and he covered
        himself with sackcloth and went into the house (temple) of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then he sent Eliakim who was in charge of his household, Shebna the
        scribe, and the elders of the priests, covered with sackcloth, to Isaiah
        the prophet the son of Amoz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They said to him, \u201CThus says Hezekiah, \u2018This is a day of
        distress and anxiety, of punishment and humiliation; for children have come
        to [the time of their] birth and there is no strength to rescue them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "It may be that the Lord your God will hear all the words of the Rabshakeh,
        whom his master the king of Assyria has sent to taunt and defy the living
        God, and will rebuke the words which the Lord your God has heard. So offer
        a prayer for the remnant [of His people] that is left [in Judah].\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So the servants of King Hezekiah came to Isaiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Isaiah said to them, \u201CSay this to your master: \u2018Thus says
        the Lord, \u201CDo not be afraid because of the words that you have heard,
        with which the servants of the king of Assyria have reviled (blasphemed)
        Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Sennacherib Defies God'
      title: Sennacherib Defies God
      number: 7
      content: "Behold, I will put a spirit in him so that he will hear a rumor and
        return to his own land. And I will make him fall by the sword in his own
        land.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the Rabshakeh returned and found the king of Assyria fighting
        against Libnah [a fortified city of Judah]; for he had heard that the king
        had left Lachish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "When the king heard them say concerning Tirhakah king of Ethiopia,
        \u201CBehold, he has come out to make war against you,\u201D he sent messengers
        again to Hezekiah, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CSay this to Hezekiah king of Judah, \u2018Do not let your God
        on whom you rely deceive you by saying, \u201CJerusalem shall not be handed
        over to the king of Assyria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Listen, you have heard what the Assyrian kings have done to all the
        lands, destroying them completely. So will you be spared? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Did the gods of the nations whom my forefathers destroyed rescue
        them\u2014Gozan and Haran [of Mesopotamia] and Rezeph and the people of Eden
        who were in Telassar? "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 13
      content: "Where is the king of Hamath, the king of Arpad [of northern Syria],
        the king of the city of Sepharvaim, and of Hena and Ivvah?\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Hezekiah received the letter from the hand of the messengers and
        read it. Then he went up to the house (temple) of the Lord and spread it
        out before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Hezekiah prayed before the Lord and said, \u201CO Lord, the God of
        Israel, who is enthroned above the cherubim [of the ark in the temple], You
        are the God, You alone, of all the kingdoms of the earth. You have made the
        heavens and the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'O Lord, bend down Your ear and hear; Lord, open Your eyes and see;
        hear the [taunting] words of Sennacherib, which he has sent to taunt and
        defy the living God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'It is true, Lord, that the Assyrian kings have devastated the nations
        and their lands '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and have thrown their gods into the fire, for they were not [real]
        gods but [only] the work of men\u2019s hands, wood and stone. So they [could
        destroy them and] have destroyed them. "
      comments: []
    - name: "19: God\u2019s Answer through Isaiah"
      title: "God\u2019s Answer through Isaiah"
      number: 19
      content: "Now, O Lord our God, please, save us from his hand so that all the
        kingdoms of the earth may know [without any doubt] that You alone, O Lord,
        are God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then Isaiah the son of Amoz sent word to Hezekiah, saying, \u201CThus
        says the Lord, the God of Israel: \u2018I have heard your prayer to Me regarding
        Sennacherib king of Assyria.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "This is the word that the Lord has spoken against him:\u2018The virgin
        daughter of ZionHas despised you and mocked you;The daughter of JerusalemHas
        shaken her head behind you!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Whom have you taunted and blasphemed?Against whom have you raised
        your voice,And haughtily lifted up your eyes?Against the Holy One of Israel!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Through your messengers you have taunted and defied the Lord,And
        have said [boastfully], \u201CWith my many chariotsI came up to the heights
        of the mountains,To the remotest parts of Lebanon;I cut down its tall cedar
        trees and its choicest cypress trees.I entered its most distant lodging,
        its densest forest.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "I dug wells and drank foreign waters,And with the sole of my feet
        I dried upAll the rivers of [the Lower Nile of] Egypt.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u2018Have you not heard [asks the God of Israel]?Long ago I did
        it;From ancient times I planned it.Now I have brought it to pass,That you
        [king of Assyria] should [be My instrument to] turn fortified cities into
        ruinous heaps.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Therefore their inhabitants were powerless,They were shattered [in
        spirit] and put to shame;They were like plants of the field, the green herb,As
        grass on the housetops is scorched before it is grown up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But I [the Lord] know your sitting down [O Sennacherib],Your going
        out, your coming in,And your raging against Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Because of your raging against Me,And because your arrogance and
        complacency have come up to My ears,I will put My hook in your nose,And My
        bridle in your lips,And I will turn you back [to Assyria] by the way that
        you came.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u2018Then this shall be the sign [of these things] to you [Hezekiah]:
        this year you will eat what grows of itself, in the second year what springs
        up voluntarily, and in the third year sow and reap, plant vineyards, and
        eat their fruit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The survivors who remain of the house of Judah will again take root
        downward and bear fruit upward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For a remnant will go forth from Jerusalem, and [a band of] survivors
        from Mount Zion. The zeal of the Lord of hosts shall perform this.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u2018Therefore thus says the Lord concerning the king of Assyria:
        \u201CHe will not come to this city [Jerusalem] nor shoot an arrow there;
        nor will he come before it with a shield nor throw up a siege ramp against
        it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "By the way that he came, by the same way he will return, and he will
        not come into this city,\u201D\u2009\u2019 declares the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u2018For I will protect this city to save it, for My own sake and
        for My servant David\u2019s sake.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Then it came to pass that night, that the angel of the Lord went
        forth and struck down 185,000 [men] in the camp of the Assyrians; when the
        survivors got up early in the morning, behold, all [185,000] of them were
        dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'So Sennacherib king of Assyria left and returned home, and lived
        at Nineveh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: It came about as he was worshiping in the house of Nisroch his god,
        that his sons Adrammelech and Sharezer killed him with a sword; and they
        escaped to the land of Ararat. And Esarhaddon his son became king in his
        place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hezekiah\u2019s Illness and Recovery"
      title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Illness and Recovery"
      number: 1
      content: "  In those days [when Sennacherib first invaded Judah] Hezekiah became
        deathly ill. The prophet Isaiah the son of Amoz came and said to him, \u201CThus
        says the Lord, \u2018Set your house in order, for you shall die and not recover.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Hezekiah turned his face to the wall and prayed to the Lord,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CPlease, O Lord, remember now [with compassion] how I have walked
        before You in faithfulness and truth and with a whole heart [entirely devoted
        to You], and have done what is good in Your sight.\u201D And Hezekiah wept
        bitterly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Before Isaiah had gone out of the middle courtyard, the word of the
        Lord came to him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CGo back and tell Hezekiah the leader of My people, \u2018Thus
        says the Lord, the God of David your father (ancestor): \u201CI have heard
        your prayer, I have seen your tears. Behold, I am healing you; on the third
        day you shall go up to the house of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I will add fifteen years to your life and save you and this city
        [Jerusalem] from the hand of the king of Assyria; and I will protect this
        city for My own sake and for My servant David\u2019s sake.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Isaiah said, \u201CBring a cake of figs. And they brought it
        and placed it on the [painful] inflammation, and he recovered.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Hezekiah said to Isaiah, \u201CWhat will be the sign that the Lord
        will [completely] heal me, and that I shall go up to the house of the Lord
        on the third day?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Isaiah said, \u201CThis will be the sign to you from the Lord, that
        He will do the thing that He has spoken: shall the shadow [indicating the
        time of day] go forward ten steps, or go backward ten steps?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Hezekiah answered, \u201CIt is easy for the shadow to go forward
        ten steps; no, but let the shadow turn backward ten steps.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Hezekiah Shows Babylon His Treasures'
      title: Hezekiah Shows Babylon His Treasures
      number: 11
      content: 'So Isaiah the prophet called out to the Lord, and He brought the
        shadow on the steps ten steps backward by which it had gone down on the sundial
        of Ahaz.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'At that time Berodach-baladan a son of Baladan, king of Babylon,
        sent letters and a gift to Hezekiah, for he had heard that Hezekiah had been
        sick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Hezekiah listened to and welcomed them and [foolishly] showed them
        all his treasure house\u2014the silver and gold and spices and precious oil
        and his armory and everything that was found in his treasuries. There was
        nothing in his house (palace) nor in all his realm that Hezekiah did not
        show them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then Isaiah the prophet came to King Hezekiah and said to him, \u201CWhat
        did these men say [that would cause you to do this for them]? From where
        have they come to you?\u201D Hezekiah said, \u201CThey have come from a far
        country, from Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Isaiah said, \u201CWhat have they seen in your house?\u201D Hezekiah
        answered, \u201CThey have seen everything that is in my house (palace). There
        is nothing in my treasuries that I have not shown them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, \u201CHear the word of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u2018Behold, the time is coming when everything that is in your
        house, and that your fathers have stored up until this day, will be carried
        to Babylon; nothing will be left,\u2019 says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u2018And some of your sons (descendants) who will be born to you
        will be taken away [as captives]; and they will become eunuchs in the palace
        of the king of Babylon.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Hezekiah said to Isaiah, \u201CThe word of the Lord which you
        have spoken is good.\u201D For he thought, \u201CIs it not good, if [at least]
        there will be peace and security in my lifetime?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The rest of the acts of Hezekiah and all his might, and how he made
        the [Siloam] pool and the aqueduct and brought water into the city, are they
        not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Hezekiah slept with his fathers [in death], and Manasseh his son became
        king in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Manasseh Succeeds Hezekiah'
      title: Manasseh Succeeds Hezekiah
      number: 1
      content: "  Manasseh was twelve years old when he became king, and he reigned
        for fifty-five years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Hephzibah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He did [great] evil in the sight of the Lord, in accordance with
        the [idolatrous] repulsive acts of the [pagan] nations whom the Lord dispossessed
        before the sons (descendants) of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For he rebuilt the high places [for the worship of pagan gods] which
        his father Hezekiah had destroyed; and he set up altars for Baal and made
        an [image of] Asherah, just as Ahab king of Israel had done, and he worshiped
        all the [starry] host of heaven and served them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he built [pagan] altars in the house (temple) of the Lord, of
        which the Lord had said, \u201CIn Jerusalem I will put My Name (Presence).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he built altars for all the host of heaven in the two courtyards
        of the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He made his son pass through the fire and burned him [as an offering
        to Molech]; he practiced witchcraft and divination, and dealt with mediums
        and soothsayers. He did great evil in the sight of the Lord, provoking Him
        to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He made a carved image of the [goddess] Asherah and set it up in
        the house (temple), of which the Lord said to David and to his son Solomon,
        \u201CIn this house and in Jerusalem [in the tribe of Judah], which I have
        chosen from all the tribes of Israel, I will put My Name forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And I will not make the feet of Israel wander anymore from the land
        which I gave their fathers, if only they will be careful to act in accordance
        with everything that I have commanded them, and with all the law that My
        servant Moses commanded them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "9: The King\u2019s Idolatries Rebuked"
      title: "The King\u2019s Idolatries Rebuked"
      number: 9
      content: 'But they did not listen; and Manasseh seduced them to do more evil
        than the nations whom the Lord destroyed before the sons (descendants) of
        Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the Lord spoke through His servants the prophets, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBecause Manasseh king of Judah has committed these repulsive
        acts, having done more evil than all the Amorites did who were before him,
        and has also made Judah sin with his idols; "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "therefore thus says the Lord, the God of Israel: \u2018Behold, I
        am bringing such catastrophe on Jerusalem and Judah, that everyone who hears
        of it, both of his ears will ring [from the shock]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I will stretch over Jerusalem the measuring line of Samaria and the
        plummet of the house of Ahab; and I will wipe Jerusalem clean just as one
        wipes a [dirty] bowl clean, wiping it and turning it upside down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will abandon the remnant (remainder) of My inheritance and hand
        them over to their enemies; and they will become plunder and spoil to all
        their enemies, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "because they have done evil in My sight, and have been provoking
        Me to anger, since the day their fathers came from Egypt to this day.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Moreover, Manasseh shed a very great quantity of innocent blood,
        until he had filled Jerusalem from one end to another; besides his sin with
        which he made Judah sin, by doing evil in the sight of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Manasseh, everything that he did, and
        the sin that he committed, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles
        of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Amon Succeeds Manasseh'
      title: Amon Succeeds Manasseh
      number: 18
      content: 'Manasseh slept with his fathers [in death] and was buried in the
        garden of his own house, in the garden of Uzza. And his son Amon became king
        in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Amon was twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned
        two years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Meshullemeth the daughter
        of Haruz of Jotbah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He also did evil in the sight of the Lord, just as his father Manasseh
        had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He walked in all the [evil] ways that his father had walked; and
        he served the idols that his father had served, and worshiped them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'he abandoned the Lord, the God of his fathers, and did not walk in
        the way of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But the servants of Amon conspired against him and killed the king
        in his own house (palace). '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then the people of the land [of Judah] killed all those who had conspired
        against King Amon, and the people of the land made his son Josiah king in
        his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Amon which he did, are they not written
        in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: He was buried in his tomb in the garden of Uzza, and his son Josiah
        became king in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Josiah Succeeds Amon'
      title: Josiah Succeeds Amon
      number: 1
      content: "  Josiah was eight years old when he became king, and reigned for
        thirty-one years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jedidah daughter
        of Adaiah of Bozkath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He did what was right in the sight of the Lord and walked in all
        the ways of his father (ancestor) David, and did not turn aside to the right
        or to the left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In the eighteenth year of King Josiah, the king sent Shaphan the
        son of Azaliah, the son of Meshullam the scribe to the house of the Lord,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CGo up to Hilkiah the high priest, so that he may count the
        entire amount of money brought into the house of the Lord, which the doorkeepers
        have collected from the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And have them deliver it to the hands of the workmen who have been
        appointed over the house of the Lord, and have them give it to the workmen
        who are in the house of the Lord to repair the damages of the house\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "that is, [have them give the money] to the carpenters and the builders
        and the masons\u2014and to buy timber and cut stones to repair the house
        (temple). "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Lost Book'
      title: The Lost Book
      number: 7
      content: "However, no accounting shall be required of them for the money placed
        in their hands, because they act faithfully.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Hilkiah the high priest said to Shaphan the scribe, \u201CI have
        found the Book of the Law in the house (temple) of the Lord.\u201D Hilkiah
        gave the book to Shaphan, and he read it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Shaphan the scribe came to the king and brought back word to him:
        \u201CYour servants have emptied out the money that was found in the house,
        and have placed it in the hands of the workmen who have been appointed over
        the house of the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Shaphan the scribe told the king, \u201CHilkiah the priest has
        given me a book.\u201D And Shaphan read it [aloud] before the king.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now when the king heard the words of the Book of the Law, he tore
        his clothes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the king commanded Hilkiah the priest, Ahikam the son of Shaphan,
        Achbor the son of Micaiah, Shaphan the scribe, and Asaiah the servant of
        the king, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Huldah Predicts'
      title: Huldah Predicts
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CGo, inquire of the Lord for my sake and for the sake of the
        people and for all Judah concerning the words of this book which has been
        found, for great is the wrath of the Lord which has been kindled against
        us, because our fathers have not listened to and obeyed the words of this
        book, so as to act in accordance with everything that is written concerning
        us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Hilkiah the priest, Ahikam, Achbor, Shaphan, and Asaiah went to
        Huldah the prophetess, the wife of Shallum the son of Tikvah, the son of
        Harhas, keeper of the wardrobe (she was living in Jerusalem, in the Second
        Quarter [the new part of the city]); and they spoke to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "She said to them, \u201CThus says the Lord, the God of Israel: \u2018Tell
        the man who sent you to me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "thus says the Lord: \u201CBehold, I am bringing a catastrophe on
        this place (Judah) and on its inhabitants, [according to] all the words of
        the book which the king of Judah has read. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Because they have abandoned (rejected) Me and have burned incense
        to other gods, that they might provoke Me to anger with all the work of their
        hands, therefore My wrath burns against this place, and it will not be quenched.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But to the king of Judah who sent you to inquire of the Lord, you
        shall say this to him: \u2018Thus says the Lord God of Israel, \u201CRegarding
        the words which you have heard, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "because your heart was tender (receptive, penitent) and you humbled
        yourself before the Lord when you heard what I said against this place and
        against its inhabitants, that they should become a desolation and a curse,
        and because you have torn your clothes and wept before Me, I have heard you,\u201D
        declares the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CTherefore, behold, [King Josiah,] I will gather you to your
        fathers, and you will be taken to your grave in peace, and your eyes will
        not see all the evil (catastrophe) which I will bring on this place.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D
        So they brought back word to the king."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Josiah\u2019s Covenant"
      title: "Josiah\u2019s Covenant"
      number: 1
      content: '  King Josiah sent word and they brought to him all the elders of
        Judah and of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The king went up to the house of the Lord, and with him all the men
        of Judah and all the inhabitants of Jerusalem, the priests, the prophets,
        and all the people, both small and great; and he read in their hearing all
        the words of the book of the covenant which was found in the house (temple)
        of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Reforms under Josiah'
      title: Reforms under Josiah
      number: 3
      content: 'The king stood by the pillar and made a covenant before the Lord,
        to walk after the Lord and to keep His commandments, His testimonies, and
        His statutes with all his heart and soul, to confirm the words of this covenant
        that were written in this book. And all the people entered into the covenant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the king commanded Hilkiah the high priest and the priests of
        the second rank and the doorkeepers to bring out of the temple of the Lord
        all the articles made for Baal, for [the goddess] Asherah, and for all the
        [starry] host of heaven; and he burned them outside Jerusalem in the fields
        of the Kidron, and carried their ashes to Bethel [where Israel\u2019s idolatry
        began]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He got rid of the idolatrous priests whom the kings of Judah had
        ordained to burn incense [to pagan gods] in the high places in Judah\u2019s
        cities and all around Jerusalem\u2014also those who burned incense to Baal,
        to the sun, to the moon, to the constellations [of the zodiac], and to all
        the [starry] host of heaven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Josiah brought out the Asherah from the house of the Lord to the
        Brook Kidron outside Jerusalem, and burned it there, and ground it to dust,
        and threw its dust on the graves of the common people [who had sacrificed
        to it]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he tore down the houses of the [male] cult prostitutes, which
        were at the house (temple) of the Lord, where the women were weaving [tent]
        hangings for the Asherah [shrines]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Josiah brought all the [idolatrous] priests from the cities
        of Judah, and desecrated the high places where the priests had burned incense
        [to idols], from Geba to Beersheba, [that is, north to south]; and he tore
        down the high places of the gates which were at the entrance of the gate
        of Joshua the governor of the city, which were on one\u2019s left at the
        city gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'However, the priests of the high places were not allowed to go up
        to the altar of the Lord in Jerusalem [to serve], but they ate unleavened
        bread among their brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Josiah also defiled Topheth, which is in the Valley of Ben-hinnom
        (son of Hinnom), so that no man could make his son or his daughter pass through
        the fire [as a burnt offering] for Molech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he got rid of the horses that the kings of Judah had given [in
        worship] to the sun at the entrance of the house of the Lord, by the chamber
        of Nathan-melech the official, which was in the annex; and he burned the
        chariots of the sun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The altars [dedicated to the starry host of heaven] which were on
        the roof, the upper chamber of Ahaz, which the kings of Judah had made, and
        the altars which Manasseh had made in the two courtyards of the house of
        the Lord, the king tore down; and he smashed them there and threw their dust
        into the Brook Kidron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The king desecrated the high places which were opposite [east of]
        Jerusalem, which were on the right (south) of the mount of corruption which
        Solomon the king of Israel had built for Ashtoreth the repulsiveness of the
        Sidonians, for Chemosh the repulsiveness of Moab, and for Milcom the repulsiveness
        of the sons (descendants) of Ammon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He broke in pieces the sacred pillars (cultic memorial stones, images)
        and cut down the Asherim and replaced them with human bones [to desecrate
        the places forever].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Further, the altar that was at Bethel, the high place which Jeroboam
        the son of Nebat, who made Israel sin, had made, even that altar and the
        high place he tore down. Then he demolished its stones, ground them to dust,
        and burned the Asherah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And as Josiah turned, he saw the graves that were there on the mountain,
        and he sent men and had the bones taken from the graves, and burned them
        on the altar and [thereby] desecrated it, in accordance with the word of
        the Lord which the man of God prophesied, who proclaimed these things [about
        this altar, naming Josiah before he was born]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Josiah said, \u201CWhat is this monument (gravestone) that I
        see?\u201D The men of the city told him, \u201CIt is the grave of the man
        of God who came from Judah and proclaimed these things which you have done
        to the altar of Bethel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "He said, \u201CLet him alone; let no one disturb his bones.\u201D
        So they left his bones undisturbed, with the bones of the prophet who came
        from Samaria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Josiah also removed all the houses of the high places which were
        in the cities of Samaria, which the kings of Israel had made provoking the
        Lord [to anger]; and he did to them just as he had done [to those] in Bethel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Passover Reinstituted'
      title: Passover Reinstituted
      number: 20
      content: 'All the priests of the high places who were there he slaughtered
        on the altars, and burned human bones on them [to desecrate the places forever].
        Then he returned to Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then the king commanded all the people, saying, \u201CCelebrate the
        Passover to the Lord your God as it is written in this book of the covenant.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Indeed, such a Passover as this had not been held since the days
        of the judges who judged Israel, nor in all the days of the kings of Israel
        and the kings of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But in the eighteenth year of King Josiah, this Passover to the Lord
        was kept in Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Moreover, Josiah removed the mediums and the soothsayers and the
        teraphim (household gods) and the idols and all the repulsive things that
        were seen in Judah and in Jerusalem, so that he might fulfill the words of
        the law written in the book which Hilkiah the priest found in the house (temple)
        of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Before him there was no king like Josiah who turned to the Lord with
        all his heart and all his soul and all his might, in accordance with all
        the Law of Moses; nor did anyone like him arise after him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'However, the Lord did not turn from the fierceness of His great wrath
        which was kindled against Judah because of all the despicable acts with which
        Manasseh had provoked Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Jehoahaz Succeeds Josiah'
      title: Jehoahaz Succeeds Josiah
      number: 27
      content: "The Lord said, \u201CI will also remove Judah from My sight, just
        as I have removed Israel; and will reject this city which I have chosen,
        this Jerusalem, and the house, of which I said, \u2018My Name [and the pledge
        of My Presence] shall be there.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Josiah, everything that he did, are they
        not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'In his days Pharaoh Neco (Necho) king of Egypt went up to the king
        of Assyria to the river Euphrates [to help him fight Nabopolassar the king
        of Babylon]. King Josiah went out to meet him, but Pharaoh killed Josiah
        at Megiddo when he saw him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Josiah\u2019s servants carried his dead body in a chariot from Megiddo,
        brought him to Jerusalem, and buried him in his own tomb. Then the people
        of the land took Jehoahaz the son of Josiah and anointed him and made him
        king in his father\u2019s place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Jehoahaz was twenty-three years old when he became king, and he reigned
        for [only] three months in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Hamutal
        daughter of Jeremiah of Libnah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord, in accordance with everything
        that his forefathers had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: Jehoiakim Made King by Pharaoh'
      title: Jehoiakim Made King by Pharaoh
      number: 33
      content: 'Pharaoh Neco imprisoned him at Riblah in the land of Hamath, so that
        he would not reign in Jerusalem, and imposed a fine on the land of a hundred
        talents of silver and a talent of gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Pharaoh Neco made Eliakim the son of Josiah king in place of his
        father Josiah, and changed his name to Jehoiakim. But he took Jehoahaz and
        brought him to Egypt, where he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Jehoiakim gave the silver and the gold to Pharaoh, but he taxed the
        land to give the money as Pharaoh commanded. He collected the silver and
        gold from the people of the land, from everyone according to his assessment,
        to give it to Pharaoh Neco.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Jehoiakim was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        for eleven years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Zebidah daughter
        of Pedaiah of Rumah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: He did evil in the sight of the Lord, in accordance with everything
        that his forefathers had done.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Babylon Controls Jehoiakim'
      title: Babylon Controls Jehoiakim
      number: 1
      content: '  In his days, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up, and Jehoiakim
        became his servant for three years; then he turned and rebelled against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord sent marauding bands of Chaldeans, Arameans (Syrians), Moabites,
        and Ammonites against Jehoiakim. And He sent them against Judah to destroy
        it, in accordance with the word of the Lord which He spoke through His servants
        the prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Surely this came on Judah at the command of the Lord, to remove them
        from His sight because of the sins of [King] Manasseh, in accordance with
        everything that he had done, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and also for the innocent blood that he shed, for he filled Jerusalem
        with innocent blood; and the Lord would not pardon it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Jehoiachin Reigns'
      title: Jehoiachin Reigns
      number: 5
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoiakim, and everything that he did,
        are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Jehoiakim slept with his fathers [in death], and his son Jehoiachin
        became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The king of Egypt did not come out of his land again, because the
        king of Babylon had taken everything that belonged to the king of Egypt,
        from the river of Egypt to the river Euphrates.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Jehoiachin was eighteen years old when he became king, and he reigned
        [only] three months in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Nehushta daughter
        of Elnathan of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Deportation to Babylon'
      title: Deportation to Babylon
      number: 9
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord, in accordance with everything
        that his father had done.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'At that time the servants of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon went
        up to Jerusalem, and the city came under siege. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came to the city while his servants
        were besieging it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Jehoiachin king of Judah surrendered to the king of Babylon, he and
        his mother and his servants and his captains and his [palace] officials.
        So the king of Babylon took him prisoner in the eighth year of his [own]
        reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He carried out of there (Jerusalem) all the treasures of the house
        (temple) of the Lord, and the treasures of the house (palace) of the king,
        and cut in pieces all the articles of gold in the temple of the Lord, which
        Solomon king of Israel had made, just as the Lord had said. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He led away into exile all Jerusalem and all the captains and all
        the brave men, ten thousand captives, and all the craftsmen and the smiths.
        None remained except the poorest people of the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Nebuchadnezzar led Jehoiachin away into exile to Babylon; also he
        took the king\u2019s mother and the king\u2019s wives and his officials and
        the leading men of the land [including Ezekiel] as exiles from Jerusalem
        to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Zedekiah Made King'
      title: Zedekiah Made King
      number: 16
      content: 'And the king of Babylon brought as exiles to Babylon all the brave
        men, seven thousand [of them], and the craftsmen and the smiths, a thousand
        [of them], all strong and fit for war.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then the king of Babylon made Mattaniah, Jehoiachin\u2019s uncle,
        king in his place, and changed his name to Zedekiah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned
        for eleven years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Hamutal daughter
        of Jeremiah of Libnah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord, in accordance with everything
        that Jehoiakim had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Because of the anger of the Lord  these things happened in Jerusalem
        and Judah, and it [finally] came to the point that He cast them from His
        presence. And Zedekiah rebelled against the king of Babylon.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Nebuchadnezzar Besieges Jerusalem'
      title: Nebuchadnezzar Besieges Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: "  Now in the ninth year of Zedekiah\u2019s reign, on the tenth day
        of the tenth month, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came, he with all his
        army, against Jerusalem, and camped against it and built siege works surrounding
        it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The city came under siege [for nearly two years] until the eleventh
        year of King Zedekiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'On the ninth day of the fourth month the famine [caused by the siege]
        was severe in the city; there was no food for the people of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the city [wall] was broken into [and conquered]; all the men
        of war fled by night by way of the gate between the two walls by the king\u2019s
        garden, though the Chaldeans (Babylonians) were all around the city. And
        they went by way of the Arabah (the plain of the Jordan). "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The army of the Chaldeans pursued the king and overtook him in the
        plains of Jericho. Then his entire army was dispersed from him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So they seized the king (Zedekiah) and brought him to the king of
        Babylon at Riblah [on the Orontes River], and sentence was passed on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Jerusalem Burned and Plundered'
      title: Jerusalem Burned and Plundered
      number: 7
      content: 'They slaughtered the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes, then put out
        the eyes of Zedekiah and bound him [hand and foot] with bronze fetters and
        brought him to Babylon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'On the seventh day of the fifth month in the nineteenth year of King
        Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon, Nebuzaradan, captain of the bodyguard, a servant
        of the king of Babylon, came to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He burned the house (temple) of the Lord, the king\u2019s house,
        and all the houses of Jerusalem; every great house he burned down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'All the army of the Chaldeans (Babylonians) who were with the captain
        of the bodyguard tore down the walls around Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Nebuzaradan the captain of the bodyguard deported [into exile]
        the rest of the people who were left in the city and the deserters who had
        joined the king of Babylon, and the rest of the multitude. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But the captain of the bodyguard left some of the unimportant and
        poorest people of the land to be vineyard workers and farmers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now the Chaldeans (Babylonians) smashed the bronze pillars which
        were in the house of the Lord and their bases and the bronze sea (large basin)
        which were in the house of the Lord, and carried the bronze to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They took away the pots, the shovels, the snuffers, the spoons, and
        all the bronze articles which were used in the temple service, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the captain of the bodyguard also took away the firepans and basins,
        anything made of fine gold and anything made of fine silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The two pillars, the one sea (large basin), and the bases which Solomon
        had made for the house of the Lord, the bronze of all these articles was
        incalculable. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The height of the one pillar was eighteen cubits (27 ft.), and a
        capital of bronze was on top of it. The height of the capital was three cubits
        (4.5 ft.); a network (lattice work) and pomegranates around the capital were
        all of bronze. And the second pillar had the same as these, with a network.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The captain of the bodyguard took [captive] Seraiah the chief priest,
        Zephaniah the second priest, and the three doorkeepers [of the temple]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And from the city [of Jerusalem] he took an officer who was in command
        of the men of war, and five men from the king\u2019s personal advisors who
        were found in the city, and the scribe of the captain of the army who mustered
        the people of the land [for military service] and sixty men from the people
        of the land who were found in the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Nebuzaradan the captain of the bodyguard took them and brought them
        to the king of Babylon at Riblah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Gedaliah Made Governor'
      title: Gedaliah Made Governor
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the king of Babylon struck them down and killed them at Riblah
        in the land of Hamath [north of Damascus]. So Judah was taken into exile
        from its land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now over the people whom Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon had left
        in the land of Judah, he appointed [as governor] Gedaliah the son of Ahikam,
        the son of Shaphan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When all the captains of the forces, they and their men, heard that
        the king of Babylon had appointed Gedaliah governor, they came with their
        men to Gedaliah at Mizpah, namely, Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, and Johanan
        the son of Kareah, and Seraiah the son of Tanhumeth the Netophathite, and
        Jaazaniah the son of the Maacathite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Gedaliah swore [an oath] to them and their men, and said to them,
        \u201CDo not be afraid of the servants (officials) of the Chaldeans. Live
        in the land and serve the king of Babylon, and it will be well with you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But in the seventh month Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, the son of
        Elishama, of the royal family [who had a claim to be governor], came with
        ten men and struck and killed Gedaliah and the Jews and the Chaldeans who
        were with him at Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then all the people, both small and great, and the captains of the
        forces set out and went to Egypt; for they were afraid of the Chaldeans (Babylonians).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now it came about in the thirty-seventh year of the exile of Jehoiachin
        king of Judah, on the twenty-seventh day of the twelfth month, that Evil-merodach
        king of Babylon, in the year that he became king, showed favor to Jehoiachin
        king of Judah and released him from prison; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and he spoke kindly to him and set his throne above the throne of
        the [other] kings [of captive peoples] who were with him in Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Jehoiachin changed his prison clothes [for palace garments] and he
        dined regularly in the king\u2019s presence for the remainder of his life; "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: and his allowance, a continual one, was given to him by the king (Evil-meridach),
        a portion every day, for the rest of his life.
      comments: []
